title: eight hour or overnight salad
directions: In a bowl, layer the lettuce, small cauliflower pieces, sliced onion and bacon bits.
Mix sugar in mayonnaise and spread over top of bacon bits sealing it to the edges.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let set overnight or at least 8 hours in refrigerator. Stir completely before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Add all other ingredients and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Carefully stir grapes, coconut, marshmallows and cherries.
Cover and chill overnight.
Arrange pear halves around the salad.

title: orange caramel nut sundaes
directions: Remove orange peel with vegetable peeler. Cut enough peel into very fine strips to measure 2 tablespoons. Transfer strips to heavy saucepan. Add sugar, juice and butter. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and boil gently until reduced to 1 cup, about 15 minutes. Cool sauce to lukewarm. Cut white pith from oranges. Slice oranges into rounds. Cut rounds into quarters. Scoop ice cream into large wine glasses. Drizzle sauce over top with oranges and toasted pecans.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread cheese mixture on tortillas (thin layer).
Roll up like jelly rolls.
Chill for 1 hour for easier slicing. Slice into 1 inch pieces.
Secure with toothpicks.
Can be eaten plain or dipped in salsa sauce.

title: scalloped potatoes(with green peppers and ham)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper (set aside).
In greased shallow 2 quart casserole layer 1/3 each of potatoes, flour mixture, green peppers and onions and ham. Repeat layers twice. Add milk. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until potatoes are done. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. (If ham is salty, reduce salt in mixture.)

title: "dog food"
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Pour over cereal.
Stir mixture together and place in a paper sack or bowl with a lid.
Add powdered sugar and shake until ingredients are well mixed.
Let cool.

title: cooked play dough(great for kids; doesn't stick.)
directions: Mix liquids in Teflon (4-quart pan).
Add dry ingredients. Let cool.

title: fructose spice cookies(makes 4 to 5 dozen)
directions: In a large bowl, stir together fructose and butter.
Mix in eggs, lemon peel and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flours, cream of tartar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves. Add to egg mixture and stir until blended.
Cover dough tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).

title: fried fish
directions: Combine corn meal,
paprika,
salt,
pepper
and
lemon rind. Dip
fish
in milk and roll in meal mixture.
Panfry in butter
or oil
in a heavy skillet until golden brown on each side.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green "make ahead" salad
directions: Mix yogurt and mayonnaise.
Thin with half and half or milk. Spread in layers in following order:
lettuce, celery, peas, yogurt and mayonnaise mix, water chestnuts, green onions and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Add shrimp just before serving.
Will keep for days in refrigerator.

title: microwave pecan bars
directions: Mix shortening and powdered sugar thoroughly. Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Press mixture firmly in oblong 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100%) for 2 minutes. Turn dish 1/4 turn.
Microwave until no longer doughy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread over hot layer.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Turn dish 1/4 turn. Microwave 3 minutes.
Cool. Cut into bars about 3 x 1-inch.
Makes 28 bars.

title: mound candy
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, coconut, margarine and Pet milk; form into balls.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate.

title: meatless casserole
directions: Place in casserole and spread 1 can of mushroom soup on top, undiluted.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix well soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and garlic with water. Cut chicken breasts thinly and stir-fry in olive oil for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables to stir-fry.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce mix.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Serves 4.

title: running board banana bread
directions: Let rise for 1/2 hour and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: greek olive spread
directions: Place all
ingredients	in
blender
until smooth paste forms. You will need to scrape down the sides often.
Refrigerate until needed.
Serve
full
strength
or	mix with sour cream or cream cheese.

title: dump salad(fruit)
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms, parsley, onion, and cooked rice in oil.
Put into a 3-pint casserole dish with broth and seasonings and cover. Bake at 350° (gas 4) for 45 minutes or until the rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little boiling, salted water until tender; drain.
In saucepan, cook carrot and onion in 4 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of bread cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all but flour together and bring to boil.
Stir in flour and knead a lot.

title: frozen orange balls
directions: Mix wafers in blender.
Mix thoroughly with remaining ingredients.
Roll in small balls, then roll in coconut.
Serve frozen.

title: one hour hot rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix oleo, sugar, salt and milk. Add dissolved yeast to mixture. Mix well. Add flour. Let set in bowl until double in size. Then put on floured wax paper or board and work. Roll out and cut or pinch out balls for rolls. Put in greased pans and bake about 30 minutes. Bake at 400° until as brown as you like them. This should make 2 dozen rolls.

title: chile cheese dip
directions: In medium baking dish, combine all ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour or microwave for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan over medium heat (sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine) and cook until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool for one minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on serving plate.
Spread shrimp sauce on cream cheese.
Spread the shrimp evenly in sauce and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain bacon.
Saute onion and celery in some of bacon drippings.
Add hamburger.
Add green pepper, garlic, tomato sauce, catsup, brown sugar, mustard and oregano.
Also add salt, pepper, lima beans, kidney beans and pork and beans.
Cook in crock-pot 8 hours on low or in roaster 2 hours at 300°.
(You can vary amount of beans.)
This is a good dish for a winter day.

title: orange delight cookies
directions: Combine Crisco and powdered sugar; add orange juice until right consistency.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix granulated sugar, flour, egg and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool completely.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Empty jello into a quart bowl.
Add boiling water to dissolve jello.
Add ice cream.
Stir gently until melted.
Add cheese and drained pineapple.
Mix evenly throughout.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Serve cold on lettuce leaf.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Recipe may be doubled.

title: taralle, barese style
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add
dry ingredients.	Add oil and mix all together until dough
is smooth.
Cut into pieces and form into circles
with
slits
horizontal
on
sides.
Drop	into boiling water and cook
until
light and float to top.
Remove from water and allow to
cool.
Then
should be hard;	if they are soggy, reboil.
Bake at
on a rack for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Boil chicken 1 hour.
Reserve broth.
Skin and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook noodles in broth.
We save a cup of broth and dump in collander.
Dump noodles back in pot and add all ingredients.
Add some broth if it looks too dry.
This will fill a 3 qt. casserole.
Cook covered for 30 minutes at 325° until bubbling.
We check at 20 minutes and usually take off the foil for the last 10 minutes to boil off some of the liquid.

title: quick cheese fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread, in saucepan; mix.
Heat on low until cheese melts and mixture is hot, stirring constantly.

title: left over ham
directions: Mix ingredients and heat.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburg and drain off fat.
Add chopped onion and garlic salt to taste.
Add both cans of soup (undiluted).
Add sour cream and parsley flakes.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: corn pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine corn, well beaten egg, sugar, salt and pepper.
To this, add half of butter (melted) and sprinkle flour into mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and dot with rest of butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Coat Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add sausage and next 3 ingredients.
Saute until tender.
Add beans and next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until heated.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.
Each serving contains 310 calories and 1.2 g fat.

title: cup pecan pies
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in flour.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen balls.
Press into miniature cupcake pans.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven bag.

title: zucchini fans
directions: Wash the zucchini; do not peel it.
Make long cuts, approximately 1/8-inch wide, down the length of each zucchini, leaving the stem end intact.
Do not cut through the last 2 inches near the stem.
Gently "fan" out the long strips and place a plate on each one to weigh it down and encourage the "fan".
Between each slice, tuck several slices or chunks of tomato, minced garlic and sprinkles of salt and pepper.
Place in a wide pan; sprinkle with oil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Just before serving, shake grated Parmesan cheese over each zucchini.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, lemon juice and cherry juice.
Put on the heat, but do not boil.
Soften gelatine in cold water; add to pineapple mixture.
Add cream cheese and chopped cherries to Cool Whip.
Mix altogether.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: roasted garlic potatoes
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Toss potatoes with remaining ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch roasting pan.
Roast for 20 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach and fruit salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and chill in refrigerator. Serve with poppy seed dressing.
You can omit the blueberries since they are hard to find.

title: snack mix
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly dressing mix, oil and herbs.
Pour and stir gently over a combination of any or all listed snacks.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Shake meat with flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag to coat well; reserve any remaining flour.
Brown beef 1/4 at a time in butter in a Dutch oven.
As beef browns, transfer it to a casserole.
Heat brandy in a small saucepan and ignite.
Pour over beef.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Sprinkle in reserved flour.
Stir in garlic, parsley and thyme to drippings in Dutch oven and brown. Add broth and wine.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over beef.
Add bay leaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: dublin coddle
directions: Cut the bacon into 1-inch/cm. squares.
Bring the stock to boil in a medium saucepan, which has a well-fitting lid.
Add the sausages and bacon; simmer for about 5 minutes.
Remove the sausages and bacon; save the liquid.
Cut each sausage into 4 or 5 pieces.
Peel the potatoes and cut into thick slices.
Skin the onions and slice them.
Assemble a layer of potatoes in the saucepan, followed by a layer of onions and then half the sausages and bacon.
Repeat the process once more and then finish off with a layer of potatoes.
Pour the reserved stock over and season lightly to taste.
Cover and simmer gently for about an hour. Adjust the seasoning and serve piping hot.
Serves 4.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Brown meat and drain. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread 1 to 2 tablespoons meat mixture. Stuff noodles with meat mixture and place in dish. Top with remaining meat mixture and grated cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Great with garlic bread.
For low-fat, use ground turkey.

title: hot currant breakfast bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and unbeaten egg.
Beat well, then add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour in greased loaf tin.
Mix currants with cinnamon and sugar and spread over top.
(Put some currants into loaf, if desired.)
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to mixture.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and add.
Mix well.
Roll mixture into 2-inch balls and flatten.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomatoes and shred cheese; combine into a large bowl.
Mix.
Brown the ground beef and season with seasoned salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Crush tortilla chips.
Combine the ground beef and tortilla chips in a large bowl of lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Mix.

title: lisbon squirrel stew
directions: Brown boneless meat with garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Add beer; allow to cool.
Combine broth and gravy, put into a crock-pot (you may need two) and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables. When vegetables are soft, add meat.
Cook on low for four hours.

title: bayou stew
directions: Saute green onions in butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: strawberry nut pie
directions: Heat marshmallows and juice of strawberries in top of double boiler until marshmallows are dissolved.
Set this mixture aside until it begins to thicken.
Add strawberries, nuts and whipped cream.
Pour this filling into the pie shell and keep the pie in refrigerator overnight.

title: merry munchies cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in top of oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: cubed steaks italiano
directions: Beat together egg and pepper.
Combine cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip each steak first in egg, then in crumb mixture.
In large skillet, add oil.
At medium heat, brown the steaks on both sides.
Reduce heat.
Add pizza sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve and sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.

title: maple-stuffed sweet potato(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes 50 to 60 minutes or until easily pierced with a fork.
Remove from oven and cool slightly. Slice potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/2-inch thick shell.
Place shells in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and transfer pulp to a food processor or blender.
Add remaining ingredients and process until smooth.
Spoon mixture evenly into shells.
Return to oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes, until heated.
A low calorie recipe.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground round and soup thoroughly.
Put
in	a
deep dish Pyrex bowl.
Mix remaining and pour
evenly
on
top
of uncooked meat loaf.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray bottoms and sides of 12 regular-size muffin cups with cooking spray.
(Spray will work better than greasing or using of paper baking cups.)
Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl with fork.
Stir in baking mix, milk and oil just until moistened.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the cheese and the ham.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cheese evenly over tops.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Wrap and refrigerate any remaining muffins.

title: poultry stuffing
directions: Saute the onions and celery in margarine.
Add chicken broth and all ingredients (except croutons).
Simmer for 10 minutes, then pour over croutons.
(If mixture seems too dry, add a little milk.) Bake in a 9 x 13-inch uncovered pan for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb slush
directions: Cut rhubarb and cook tender in water.
Strain juice and add jello, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix until dissolved and freeze. Thaw to slush and add ginger ale.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line a 9 x 9-inch square pan with pastry.
Add other ingredients.
Top with pastry and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy and light.
Slowly add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours until firm, then top with cherry pie filling or your favorite topping.
Makes 1 pie.

title: shrimp and crab soup
directions: Wash peppers.
Remove ribs and seeds; cut into small pieces. Slice carrots thinly crosswise.
Break up tomatoes with fork. Stud onion with cloves.
In large saucepan, bring 3 cups water and chicken broth to boiling.
Add peppers, carrot, tomato, onion, green onion, celery, basil, thyme, bay leaf and hot dried pepper (optional).
Return to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and lemon.
Cook gently, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add parsley at end of cooking time. Serve.
Makes about 2 quarts, 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix, then add nuts.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat 5 cups of milk until it begins to steam.
Mix the remaining cup of milk with the cornmeal until it is smooth.
Add to hot milk, stirring constantly.
This prevents lumps forming. Add butter and stir until melted.
Cook 15 minutes over low heat, stirring frequently.
The mixture will become as thick as breakfast cereal.
Beat together the molasses, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, salt and eggs.
Spoon about 1/4 cup cornmeal mixture into the molasses mixture, beating until blended.
Slowly add another cup or two of hot cornmeal, then beat the mixture into remaining hot cornmeal.
Pour into buttered 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Bake for 2 hours.
Cool at least 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds.
Pour in pan.
Bake until pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.

title: sauerkraut, crock jar method
directions: Shred cabbage finely and put 2 1/2 quarts of it (firmly packed) and 3 1/2 tablespoons salt in a large pan and mix.
Pack firmly in crock with a potato masher. Fill crock to 4 to 5-inches from top.
Press firmly enough so juice covers cabbage.
Cover with clean cloth and place a plate on top.
Weight down with a jar of water.
Clean cloth occasionally to keep off mold and scum. When bubbling stops (after 2 or 3 weeks), tap the crock gently. If no bubbles rise, fermentation is over.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, and syrup in a heavy saucepan. Bring to boil, cover and cook for 3 minutes. Uncover and cook while stirring, until mixture reaches 230 degrees on a candy thermometer. Remover from heat and let stand for 15 minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup. Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Continue stirring until candy boils. Slowly place thermometer in syrup. Boil, without stirring, to 265°, hard-ball stage.

title: anna's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups of warm water in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover bowl tightly; refrigerate.
When ready to use, spoon dough into greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes about 2 to 3 dozen.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, salt and onions to bacon grease.
Add bacon and heat through.
Add cabbage and water.
Steam until tender.

title: cranberry warmer
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Microwave at High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Strain and pour into serving cups.

title: special cup cakes
directions: Mix together by hand. Bake in 350 degrees oven 35 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Dough should be very cold and stiff.
Make into walnut size balls. Flatten tops slightly and place onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together white and brown sugars. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Squish in 3 pounds peanut butter.
Stir together oatmeal, flour and baking soda in separate bowl and then mix with gooey stuff.
Mix in remaining ingredients by hand.
Shape cookies 1/2-inch thick, 5 to 6 inches in diameter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet about 20 minutes, until edges begin to turn brown.
Do not overbake or you will have made expensive rocks!

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix and drop by big tablespoons on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Can be baked in muffin tins.

title: mexican dish
directions: Grate cheese.

Put layer of crushed chips, layer of filling, layer of cheese, then repeat layers of chips, filling and cheese. Heat to bubbly around edges and to where cheese has melted at 350°, approximately 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Roll in chopped dried beef and serve.

title: fresh tomato soup(mom's summer recipe)
directions: Place
tomatoes and onion in large saucepan.
Cover and bring to
a
boil.
Add
seasonings
and
simmer
for 1 hour. Remove from heat and pass through a strainer or press.
Place strained tomatoes
and
all
juice in saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add 1/4 cup to 1/2 cup uncooked rice to soup and simmer until rice is overcooked.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer
alternate layers of crumbs and squash mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with crumbs.
Use the melted butter to mix with the crumb mixture.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour. Serve.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Mix egg whites, cake mix, pie filling, water and almond extract. Mix all ingredients well and pour in baking dish to bake for 25-30 minutes.
Let cake cool.
This is a very moist cake.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the cookies in large plastic bag or in food processor. Cream the butter, sugar and cream cheese.
In another bowl cream the milk, instant pudding and thawed whipped topping.
Combine the two mixtures.
Alternate layers of the mixture and the cookie crumbs, starting and ending with the cookie crumbs.
Top with cherries, if desired.
Chill.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place meat in pan; place vegetables on top.
Sprinkle tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper over all.
Pour V-8 juice on top.
Cover and cook at 250° for 5 hours.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 19-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and garnish as desired. Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: tangy chipped beef ball
directions: Mix well.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup of dried beef (reserve remaining for coating.)
Chill one hour and form ball. Roll in remaining dried beef.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease plate.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut candy in small pieces.
Mix dates, candy, nuts and 1/2 cup flour; set aside.
Cream oleo with sugar; add eggs one at a time. Blend well.
Add buttermilk.
Fold in candy mixture.
Stir well and add coconut.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in large saucepan and bring to boil.
Remove when cauliflower is tender.
Cool.
Cut in pieces and dip in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Fry in skillet of shortening.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix milk, fat, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cook to lukewarm.
Stir in egg and yeast.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Gradually stir in more flour until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: hearty corned beef salad
directions: Combine boiling water and gelatin in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in vinegar and refrigerate until slightly thickened (about 1 hour).
Break up corned beef with fork.
Stir corned beef and remaining ingredients into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until set (about 2 hours).

title: sherbet pies
directions: Beat cream cheese in bowl.
Add 1/2 tub of cool whip and softened sherbet.
Mix together and pour into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Keep pies frozen.

title: no cook pickles(ice box bread and butter pickles)
directions: Add salt to first 3 ingredients and stir well.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain.

title: blueberry cream pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Line pie crusts with slices of bananas.
Mix confectioners sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread a layer over bananas. Top with the blueberry filling.
Garnish with small spoons of Cool Whip.

title: fluffy pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in pie crust.
Top with 1 container of Cool Whip.

title: pork tenderloin diane
directions: Press each tenderloin in 1-inch slice; sprinkle surface with lemon pepper.
Heat butter in skillet and cook tenderloin slices on each side until done.
Remove them to platter.
In skillet, combine lemon juice, Worcestershire and mustard and cook, stirring with pan juices, until heated through.
Pour sauce over meat; sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Combine meat, onion and bell pepper; cook until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings and mix well.
Pour into a large greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can add grated cheese to top casserole and bake until cheese melts.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well, adding apples and pecans last.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Slice chuck roast thin.
Simmer all ingredients until tender and sauce thickens.
Add more water if meat is tough or sauce is too thick.

title: bean pot
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and green pepper; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into dish; bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade; stir in lemon juice and condensed milk.
Fold in whipped topping until smooth.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.
Keep in the freezer and it makes a great last minute treat for company.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix crumb ingredients (flour, shortening, brown sugar and salt) together.
Set aside 1 cup.
Mix ingredients for liquid (molasses, baking soda and hot water) and combine with crumbs. Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This cake has a moist bottom like the Shoo-Fly Pie.

title: bouquet garni no. 1
directions: Put herbs in the middle of a coffee filter.
Gather up into a bag and tie with string.
Store garni in an airtight glass jar. Use to flavor soups or stews.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add Cool Whip and mix well. Add lemonade mix and sugar and beat thoroughly.
Chill until ready to serve.
(Good dip for strawberries, blueberries, blackberries, cantaloupe, honeydew melon, grapes, apples, oranges, etc.)

title: corn and oyster casserole
directions: Layer cracker crumbs, corn and oysters.
Dot with butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Add oyster juice to milk.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake until it looks done.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine wet ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix the 2 together only until moist.
Batter will be lumpy.
Cook on hot skillet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli well.
Add cottage cheese, flour and oleo.
Add eggs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Cream together butter, cheese and salt.
Blend in sour cream, chives and cucumber.
Spoon over vegetables.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: date nut bread(bread and butter sandwiches)
directions: Cut up dates and pour the boiling water over.
Add baking soda and cool for 20 minutes.
Beat in sugar, eggs and pecans.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients and add to date mixture.
Stir until just blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Slice thinly and spread with butter (not margarine).
Cut into dainty little sandwiches.

title: quesadillas
directions: Place a tortilla in a preheated skillet (medium heat).
Turn tortilla once and spread enough cheese to cover half of the tortilla.
Fold tortilla in half.
Continue to turn tortilla over until the cheese melts.

title: popcorn ball syrup
directions: Stir all together, except vanilla.
Add the vanilla.
Cook to 260° on candy thermometer.
Pour over popped corn.
Roll into balls.

title: tasty macaroni and beef
directions: Using large frying pan, cook onion and peppers until tender. Add garlic and beef and cook meat until brown.
Add soup, tomatoes, bouillon, water and salt.
Simmer until all ingredients are well mixed.
Turn off heat.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix with meat mixture and serve.
Serves 6.

title: ham omelet
directions: Use as much ham, bell pepper, onions and cheese as desired.

title: siamese chicken salad
directions: Remove skin from breast, thighs and legs.
Rub into the meat a mix of the curry, cloves and ginger.
Let meat rest for 1/2 hour. Put leftover pieces of chicken and giblets into a pot.
Barely cover with water.
Put prepared meat on top and gently poach for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Dice meat and mix well with the pineapple, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Mix with dressing made of sour cream, mayonnaise, Tabasco and pineapple juice.
When ready to serve, top with peanuts.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix the lukewarm water, sugar and salt.
Sprinkle the dry yeast over the top.
Let yeast dissolve.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 1 cup water.
Add	applesauce
and heat. Add large package of cherry or strawberry jello and one can crushed pineapple.	Let set overnight.

title: mother's buttermilk salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple in a saucepan and beat until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let this mixture cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk. Add to this the Jell-O mixture and the nuts.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: cocktail sauce for seafood
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grate 1/2 of German chocolate; mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Melt the other half of German chocolate and pour over cake while hot.
Cook in a tube pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and pinch of salt, while adding sugar, a little at a time.
Add butter, syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm when gently shaken.

title: earth grains bread
directions: Combine milk
and water.
Heat to 105° to 115°.
Put in a large bowl. Dissolve yeast in warm mixture. Add brown sugar, oats, salt,
whole
wheat
flour,
rye
flour, 1 cup flour and sunflower seeds.
Stir vigorously 1 minute. Stir in 1 1/2 cups more flour to	make
a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface using rest of flour until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes. Place in buttered bowl and
butter top of dough. Cover and let rise in warm place until
double
in
bulk.
Punch down.
Form into 2 loaves.	Place in	greased
loaf pans. Brush with milk. Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake
in slow oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until it sounds hollow when tapped.

title: overnight turkey
directions: Place turkey in crock pot.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over turkey, add a little salt and pepper.
Cook overnight on high, turn on low the following morning.
Should be done in 12 hrs.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Put carrots, onions and celery in bottom of crock-pot.
Add whole chicken.
Top with salt, pepper and liquid.
Sprinkle basil over top.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off pepper; remove stems and set tops aside.
Clean out seeds.
Preheat pot over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Brown ground beef; remove from heat.
Add onions, celery, rice, milk, egg, salt, pepper and chili powder to beef and mix.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
In pot, combine tomato soup and water.
Place pepper tops in bottom of pot; set stuffed peppers on tops to prevent from spilling.
Place pot on stove and simmer, covered, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Spoon sauce over peppers when serving.

title: wassail
directions: Tie whole spices in a cloth bag (or can substitute 2 1/4 teaspoons each of ground spices).
Simmer all ingredients 15 minutes.
Remove spices and serve hot.
Simmer as long as your holiday party lasts.
The aroma is wonderful and the flavor just deepens.

title: linguica and peppers
directions: Note:
All amounts may be changed to taste.

title: herb bread
directions: Put Swiss cheese between slices of bread.
Cover with butter mixture, thick!
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes or until beginning to brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: In a large bowl, put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine margarine, cocoa, Coca-Cola and marshmallows in a saucepan and heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir until marshmallows are dissolved.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In layers, add other vegetables.
Do not toss.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over layers.
Sprinkle with sugar and cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle bacon over salad before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and Crisco together.
Combine remaining ingredients with first mixture.
This makes 3 single or 1 double and a single.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: pimento cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with fresh vegetables.
Yields 1 cup.

title: country style ribs with ragu sauce
directions: Cut ribs in halves or quarters.
Place in large crock-pot. Cover with Ragu spaghetti sauce.
(I place 1/2 the meat in and cover with 1/2 sauce, then add remaining meat and sauce.)
Slow cook for 12 hours.

title: garbanzo and chorizo
directions: Simmer until done.
Serve with tomato sauce, if desired.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions in 9 x 13-inch dish. While hot, out of oven, punch holes all through cake.
Spread with sweetened condensed milk.
Spread with caramel topping.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of Heath bar chips over cake.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining Heath Bar chips.
May make 24 hours ahead.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean out mushrooms and keep stems.
Stuff mushrooms with sausage and bake in casserole dish 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple meatballs
directions: Make meatballs from first 7 ingredients.
Cook in skillet or in microwave.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook until thickened and boils. Add meatballs and pineapple chunks.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into greased baking dish and let set on counter for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° until done in middle, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: desi delight
directions: Take a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and open up one crescent roll. Lay it width way and unroll it.
Spread on the bottom of a sprayed pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and a small amount of milk to make it creamy; add flavoring.
Spread this into pan, then take 2 rolls and open up and spread on top of filling, spreading crust to all sides. Bake at 350° or until golden brown.
Make a confectioners sugar and milk glaze and pour over top.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onions.
Add other ingredients, except cilantro, tortillas, cheese and avocado.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
To serve, sprinkle with cilantro, tortillas, grated cheese and avocado. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Spread margarine evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add a little butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Combine egg, Wesson oil and sugar.
Add 3 cups self-rising flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each roll in melted butter and fold into pocketbook rolls.
Let rise 2 hours. Bake in hot oven, 450°, for about 8 minutes or until done.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix with boiling water.
Fry slow in thin grease.

title: teriyaki sauce marinade
directions: Marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Grill or broil.
Slice against grain in strips and serve with rice or cube as hors d'oeuvre.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Blend 3 to 5 minutes in blender.
Dough will be sticky.
Put dough into 1 pound well-greased coffee cans, including lids.
Let rise in a warm place until lids pop off.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Makes two cans.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Melt butter; add rhubarb and 1 cup of sugar.
Cook slowly until rhubarb is tender.
Add the gelatin.
Combine 1 cup of sugar, cornstarch, salt, beaten egg yolks and cream.
Add to rhubarb and cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue made from 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: roasted sweet potatoes and apple caramel sauce
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Place potatoes in a 2-quart microwave-safe baking dish. Cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes, turning potatoes once halfway through. Let stand 10 minutes. While potatoes stand, combine juice, sugar, cinnamon and ginger slice in small saucepan. Over high heat, bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Boil 10 minutes or more until mixture thickens to a light syrup consistency; let cool. Remove cinnamon stick and ginger slice and discard. Stir in cider vinegar.

title: chess pie
directions: Make or buy pie
shell.
Melt
margarine and cool.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour	into
uncooked pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until knife comes out clean.

title: picnic chicken
directions: Crush crackers.
Combine with seasonings.
Divide mixture in half and put in pie tin, set aside.
Beat eggs with milk in shallow pan.
Roll chicken pieces in crumb mixture, then in beaten eggs and then in crumbs.
Place in shallow pan, skin side up.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, do not turn.
Good hot or cold.

title: hungarian chicken paprikas
directions: Saute onion in shortening until golden.
Add paprika, stirring well to blend.
Do not let the paprika scorch.
Add chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Add water; mix well.
Cover and let simmer until tender.
Remove chicken; add sour cream to drippings in pan and mix well.
Heat, but do not boil, as this will cause sour cream to curdle.
Return chicken to pan and keep warm.
Serve over noodles, rice or best of all, over tiny dumplings.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Mix brownie batter, using 3 or the eggs.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar, 2 eggs, flour and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour half of brownie batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie batter.
Spoon remaining brownie batter here and there over the cream cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook whole potatoes in large amount of boiling water for about 14 minutes or until tender.
Drain and remove skin.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
Melt butter and brown sugar in large skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Add potatoes and toss until well coated.
Cover skillet.
Simmer over low heat for 9 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 6 minutes longer.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Cut up or grate cheese and put in crock-pot.
Pour in taco sauce on top of cheese; add hamburger. Stir and cook on high until all cheese is melted.
Cook on low as you serve with Tostitos.

title: chocolate quad
directions: Mix flour, very soft butter and 1/2 cup pecans to make dough. Pat with hands to cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool!
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Beat pudding and milk until smooth and spread on top of second layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top as fourth layer.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chocolate shavings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour until smooth; beat. The more you beat the better the cake is.
Use a cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't even walk on the floor.
This cake is very sensitive.
Don't substitute anything in this cake.

title: holiday mix
directions: Melt butter and bacon drippings in pan.
Add remaining seasonings.
Stir.
Put cereal and remaining ingredients in 2 large trays.
Pour sauce over cereal evenly.
Bake 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pat's chicken and linguine
directions: Brown chicken in skillet; remove and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients except chicken.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, then uncover and simmer about 5 more minutes.
Stir in chicken and cooked linguine.
Heat through and serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter. Heat 3 cups of milk.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and 3 eggs. Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over bread.
Add hot milk to egg mixture.
Pour over bread.

title: taco soup
directions: Put tomatoes, chili beans, hominy and Ro-Tel in large pot. (Do not drain.)
Let simmer while preparing ground beef mixture. In small amount of oil, saute onions.
(You may add some bell pepper, if you want to.)
Add ground beef.
Brown.
Drain off fat. Add taco seasoning mix and 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer a few minutes, then add to other mixture.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Put tortilla chips in bottom of bowl.
Add soup.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar good, then add the rest.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat whites of eggs in medium bowl on high speed until stiff peaks form; set aside.
Beat flour, baking soda, sugar, butter, oil, buttermilk, coconut extract, vanilla and 2 2/3 cups flaked coconut in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into round cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pans, then remove and cool completely. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in greased baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cayenne together and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: banana-nut salad
directions: Toss the sliced bananas in the lemon juice.
Add the walnuts to the bananas.
Mix the mayonnaise with the parsley and add to the bananas and walnuts.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves. Serves 4.

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Pour condensed milk and cream cheese into bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Add lemon juice as you like.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 45 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Parboil zucchini in salted water.
Cool.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 stuffing mixture. Reserve rest.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add drained and cooled zucchini.
Spread mixture over stuffing.
Spread reserved stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gooey cake 2
directions: Beat 1 egg, mix with yellow cake mix and melted butter or margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 2 eggs, cream cheese and lemon juice together until light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar, pecans and coconut.
Blend well.
Pour into pan over first mixture.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons powdered sugar over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: black forest cake
directions: Prepare devil's food cake mix as directed. Bake batter in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Cool on rack.
Place one cooled layer on a serving plate. Spread
1/2 can of cherries on cake layer. Top with second layer. Combine cream, sugar, vanilla and orange rind. Whip until cream is thick and holds its shape. Spread whipped cream on sides and top of cake.
Spread 1/2 can of cherries on top of whipped cream. Sprinkle with chocolate shavings. Chill before serving.

title: aunt lucy's cherry salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add to Cool Whip mixture. Place in refrigerator overnight in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.

title: kaaldolmer(stuffed cabbage leaves with meat)
directions: Cut the core out of cabbage and cook in salted water 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove
leaves.
Simmer rice in milk 40 minutes.
Cool.
Mix
pork,
veal
and salt; gradually beat
in one egg
white
at
a
time.
Beat
vigorously.
(Use electric beater if possible.)
Stir in white pepper and onion. Mix in rice mixture for creamy smooth filling.
Put tablespoon meat on each leaf.
Roll
over
once,
turn sides over filling (can fasten with toothpick).
Arrange
rolls
in
buttered 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add
beef
consomme
and spread each roll with 1/2 teaspoon of
molasses.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven, then turn rolls over and bake another 30 minutes.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut squash into 1/2-inch slices and arrange in ungreased casserole dish.
Top with sliced apples.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over top.
Bake, covered, for about an hour.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican tuna dip
directions: Note:
Other sliced vegetables such as broccoli, zucchini, mushrooms and cauliflower can be used.

title: fruit crumb cake
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese, eggs, Milnot, butter, and vanilla.
Stir together dry ingredients in another bowl, then add to batter.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased cake pan.
Place preserves in spoonfuls on top of batter.
Cover preserves with remainder of batter.
Bake for 45 mins. at 350°.

title: grilled tuna steaks
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over tuna steaks. Marinate for 1 hour. Grill to desired doneness.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger until crumbly.
Drain grease.
Stir in taco mix.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix up corn bread mix.
Carefully top the meat mixture with corn bread mix.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Cover with topping.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Arrange chicken in long shallow baking dish.
Add the rice. Mix together 3 soups and water and pour over the chicken and rice. Sprinkle with curry powder.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice and chicken are tender.
May use water chestnuts for variety.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli in chicken stock until tender.
Stir in the Cup-a-Soup packages and the half and half.
Add the cheese until melted.
Stir to thoroughly mix ingredients.
At this time, mix the cornstarch with a small amount of water and add to the soup for desired thickness.
(You can add a can of cream of mushroom soup at this time if you want a thicker soup.)

title: chocolate cake(from scratch)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake in loaf pan at 375° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: one-step yogurt pound cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Pour batter into greased and floured 6 cup Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool for 15 minutes in pan. Remove and continue to cool on rack.
Serves 12.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute vegetables and seasonings in oil.
Mix with bread, eggs, sage and cheese.
Put in casserole.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Add another 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook until melted.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add other ingredients, except macaroni and cheese dinner. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions.
Add to other ingredients; mix lightly and simmer for approximately 15 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium pan, combine water, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
With a wooden spoon, beat in flour all at once.
Return to low heat.
Continue beating until mixture forms a ball and leaves the side of pan. Remove from heat; beat in eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each.
Continue beating until dough is shiny and breaks into strands.
Drop by rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and brown (45 to 50 minutes). Puffs should sound hollow when tapped.
Let cool completely on rack away from draft.
Cut off tops and fill with pudding, jelly, whipped cream or whatever and replace tops.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature; grate into mixing bowl. After all cheeses are grated, add other ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into 3 balls.
On wax paper, sprinkle garlic and paprika and roll ball over wax paper.
Wrap balls in wax paper and refrigerate.
Nuts or other desired coating can be used to roll the cheese balls.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple juice, eggs and sugar in a medium saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Cool slightly. Add pineapple and remaining ingredients, except the whipped cream; stir well.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: sausage-bean soup
directions: Heat cooking oil in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add onion and garlic. Saute lightly.
Remove from oil and set aside.
Add chopped meat to pan and brown; remove and set aside.
Brown sausage links and remove; cut into bite-size chunks and set aside.
Pour strained tomatoes into oil, stirring gently and let simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery and cook another 5 minutes.
Return all cooked ingredients, stirring to let meats absorb sauce.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add seasonings to taste.
Pour in water and add beans; cook for another 1/2 hour.
Meanwhile, cook elbow macaroni.
When soup is done, add cooked macaroni and stir.
Serve immediately.
May sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: aunt helen's coffee cake
directions: Generously grease a 12-cup nonstick Bundt pan with butter or margarine.
Dust with flour and shake off excess.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain blueberries and set aside.

title: spicy pickles
directions: Slice pickles 3/4-inch, then into 4 pieces.
Layer pickles, sugar, Tabasco sauce and garlic into 12 to 13-inch crockery bowl. Stir once a day for 5 days.
Put in jars on sixth day and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake in pie shell at 350° until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease 11 x 7inch baking dish. Place potatoes in large saucepan. Cover with water, bring to a boil.
Cook over medium-high heat for 3 to 4 minutes, drain. Set aside.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour,	cocoa,	baking	powder,
soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream together margarine and sugar until they are smoothly
blended.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
addition.	Stir in vanilla and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients alternately
with
milk.
Add nuts.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately
1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Turn
over	on
wire
rack	to
cool
thoroughly. Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: cool lime pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add lime rind and juice.
Pour
into bowl, cover with plastic wrap and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 1 hour or refrigerate 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and lime slices, if desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Wash good. Cover with water. Bring potatoes to a boil and cook 15 minutes. Rinse and drain well. Place in freezer for 10 minutes. Dice boiled eggs fine. Coat potatoes with diced eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well with fork. Place in refrigerator. Serve chilled or serve immediately.

title: jambalaya
directions: Season and brown chicken in oil (lard, bacon drippings) over medium-high heat.
Add sausage to pot and saute with chicken. Remove broth from pot.
For brown jambalya, either add heaping tablespoon brown sugar to hot oil and caramelize, make roux or use Kitchen Bouquet.
For red jambalya, delete this.
Saute onions, celery, green pepper and garlic to the tenderness that you desire. Return chicken and sausage to pot.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Beat for 5 minutes with electric mixer.

title: cow cookies
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, shortening, margarine, vanilla and egg in a medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
Mix chocolate into 1 part dough; divide chocolate dough into 2 equal parts.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients except Fritos and cheese.	Refrigerate overnight.	Add
Fritos and cheese and toss just before serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges and cut up.
To oranges, add coconut.
Add sugar. Add few cherries for color.
Refrigerate and let set overnight. May add crushed pineapple, if you like.

title: cool summer dessert
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with non-stick spray.
Spread cookie mix into cake pan evenly. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
(Do not over bake.)
Remove from oven and cool.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread over cooled cookie bar.
Top with your favorite sliced fresh fruits.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.
Cut and serve.
(For calorie counters, use light Cool Whip and light cream cheese.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange layers of potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole and cover with onions.
Sprinkle with some of flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with some of butter.
Repeat layers until all are used, ending with potatoes and butter. Pour milk all over.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Add grated cheese to each of the layers.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Whip cheese and sugar together; add eggs one at a time.
Bake in ungreased pie pan for 45 minutes at 325°.
Then add topping and bake a few minutes longer.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onions in large pan until beef is brown.
Drain and stir in sauce mix, water, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles and vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water.
Cool.
Blend cheese with cream; add pecans.
Roll mixture into small balls. Place
balls in mold.
Pour strawberries over balls.
Pour gelatin over all.
Chill until firm.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Set aside while you scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and margarine to hot milk.
When cool, add parts of flour and beat well.
Add well beaten eggs and yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour.
Let rise to double in bulk.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine in baking dish. Put oil in bottom or spray with Pam.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onion and green pepper.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, corns, pimento and corn bread mix.
Put mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; spoon the sauteed onion and pepper over top, then 1/2 pint sour cream in dollops.
Cover with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: great crab cakes
directions: In a bowl, break bread into small pieces and moisten with milk.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Shape into cakes. Melt two tablespoons butter with two tablespoons oil and fry crab cakes until golden brown (about seven minutes each side). Makes six small cakes or four large cakes.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Cook chicken; do not add salt.
Debone when cool and cut into eating pieces.
Place meat in large casserole that has been buttered (I use Pam).
Spread soups over chicken.
Saute onion and celery and sprinkle over soups.
Top with stuffing mix and spoon chicken broth over the mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: banana pickles
directions: Pare large cucumbers; cut the long way.
Using a teaspoon, cut out the seeds.
Bring syrup to boil.
Pack cucumbers into jars. Pour syrup over cucumbers.
Cold pack for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Set the gelatin mix in a pan of water and boil until clear.
Combine the eggs and gelatin and let set until like soft custard (do not let congeal).

title: firehouse spaghetti
directions: Start cooking with tomato sauce.
Add Ro-Tel, canned tomatoes and mushrooms.
Brown ground beef and cook pork slowly until tender.
Add the ground beef and pork to sauce.
Saute onions and add to sauce.
Add water to reach desired thickness.
After sauce comes to a boil, reduce heat and cook 2 hours.
About 30 minutes before serving, add cooked vermicelli (thin spaghetti) and package of spaghetti sauce mix.
You may substitute chicken in place of pork or use both.

title: kraut salad
directions: Toss, eat and enjoy.

title: cherry cake
directions: Add cherry juice to Carnation evaporated milk (other brands change the taste of the cake).
Cream butter and sugar, add evaporated milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla and beat.
Mix nuts and cherries and roll in 1/2 cup of flour, then add to the mixture.
Next add beaten egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° around 45 to 50 minutes.
Ice with butter icing (add a little cherry juice and food coloring as part of the liquid).
Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, chocolate and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each one for 5 minutes (no cheating here).
Put in a cooled pie shell; top with whipping cream and nutmeats if you wish.
Enjoy!

title: red beans
directions: Cook beans in water, adding ham bone for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then add sausage, onion, garlic, celery and bay leaves.
Continue to cook over low heat for 1/2 to 1 hour.
If beans become dry, add heated water.
Serve on a mound of rice.

title: sweet apple cider cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add currants.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Beat thoroughly.

title: haluski
directions: Grate potatoes; add salt, egg and flour to make a soft dough. Have a pot of water (3-quart) boiling.
Put dough on plate and scrape off with teaspoon into water.
Stir often and gently.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and pecans. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: sonora chicken casserole
directions: Grate cheeses; set aside.
Tear corn tortillas into pieces. Set aside.
Layer all in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish: 1/2 tortillas, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, 1/2 stick margarine and 1 egg.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together pumpkin, 3 eggs, milk, brown sugar and cinnamon and mix until smooth.
Pour on top of first mixture.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll in chopped pecans.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Measure sifted flour and sift with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.
Set aside.
Melt shortening in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add sugar; mix well.
Cool slightly. Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Then add flour mixture, a little at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: lea-olde spice cake
directions: Butter one 9-inch cake pan.
Lightly coat with dry bread crumbs.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Remove seasoning packet from noodles and set aside.
Crunch noodles (don't cook) and combine with next four ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine seasoning packet with remaining ingredients and mix with a wire whisk.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill at least overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, corn, flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry candies
directions: Lightly oil a baking sheet or marble slab as well as 2 teaspoons, set aside.
Spread pecans in a single layer in a microwavable baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, on High until toasted, about 5 minutes.
In a 2-quart glass measure, stir together the sugar, corn syrup, heavy cream and salt.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and cook on High for 5 minutes.
Pierce plastic to allow steam to escape.
Uncover in oven and stir with a wooden spoon.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 4 more minutes.
Stir the toasted pecans and vanilla into the caramel.
Using the oiled spoons, drop caramel mixture a teaspoon at a time onto baking sheet.
Break chocolate into 1-ounce pieces and put into a 2 cup microwavable container.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and cook on High until just melted, about 2 1/2 minutes.
Uncover and stir. When candies are firm enough to handle and chocolate is partially cooled, dip the clusters in the chocolate and put on sheets of parchment or waxed paper.
Let stand in a cool place until chocolate has hardened.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 dozen candies.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mash cream cheese.
Stir in all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Season with Lawry's seasoned salt to taste.
Bake in a shallow pan at 250° for 1 hour.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook salt pork in 1 tablespoon butter, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes or until fat is rendered.
Remove cracklings to another bowl.
In fat remaining, cook onion and celery until softened.
Add 1 1/2 cups clam liquid, cubed potatoes and enough water to cover potatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk, heavy cream and seasonings.
Simmer, add remaining 1 tablespoon butter.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, vanilla, nuts and peanut butter.
Blend or stir well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes 3 dozen.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a crock-pot, which has been greased with 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Cut several thin slices of cheese and put on top.
Cook for 4 hours on low.

title: coconut cake
directions: 1. Add first 5 ingredients and beat 4 minutes.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Press in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes; cool.

title: german supper
directions: Cut sausage into 2-inch chunks.
In large kettle boil all ingredients.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Good with pumpernickel bread on a cold evening.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Do not cover or stir.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Finely chop onion, red pepper and celery.
Chop basil leaves to measure 1 tablespoon; reserve remaining basil for garnish.

title: deep dish tuna pie
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions.
In separate saucepan, add soup.
Add drained peas to soup.
Add tuna and onions.
Heat to serving temperature.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes around edge and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix the Crisco, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Sift and mix into this mixture the flour, soda, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
Add the coconut, oatmeal, pecans and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place on wax paper until cookie is cool.

title: chicken vegetable and rice soup(number of servings: 10)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan.
Bring to a boil; turn heat down and simmer for five minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: saucy little meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small individual loaves. Cover with the following topping.

title: sugar-free teriyaki sauce(diabetic free food)
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight lid.
Refrigerate. Will keep several weeks.
Great with chicken, pork or beef.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add Kahlua and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fruit:
Granny Smith apples, bananas, winter pears, etc.

title: easy fruitcake
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Combine raisins, peaches, shortening, sugar and orange juice in a saucepan and heat just to boiling.
Remove from heat; pour into large bowl.
Cool.
Add candies, fruits and nuts to cooled mixture.
Stir in beaten eggs. Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves together.
Beat into fruit-nut mixture.
Spoon batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until cakes test done.
Decorate to your liking.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
In another pan, melt oleo.
Stir in flour, sugar and eggs. Add bell pepper, bacon, pimento and cheese.
Add pepper to taste. Mix with corn and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add spices, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Allow to simmer while cooking lasagna noodles.
Don't overcook noodles.
(I like to slightly undercook, the noodles handle better.)
Add vinegar to water for noodles.
This will help the noodles from sticking together.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan or larger, ending with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: mary jeanette's cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and unbeaten eggs well.
Add warm water with soda dissolved and vanilla; mix, then add flour until dough is stiff enough to handle with hands.
Roll up in little balls and press fairly flat with a fancy bottom of dish dipped in granulated sugar.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter and sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: cajun deviled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients with egg yolks.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl beat first four ingredients together well. Then fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into the ready serve pie crust. Freeze for a minimum of four hours. Thaw ten minutes before serving. Top with chocolate sauce and chopped nuts. Yummy!

title: artichoke dip
directions: Squeeze water from artichokes and chop.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 15-25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: apple snack cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar and oil.
Mix until light yellow.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture.
This will be very stiff.
Add vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken divan(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Simmer chicken until tender in oil with chopped onion.
Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayo, cheese and seasonings. Drain broccoli and place in bottom of a greased 3-quart dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over that.
Next, add chicken and sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Next, spread on mix. Sprinkle on top with more Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (do not cover).

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Saute onions 5 minutes.
Add sliced zucchini.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes and 5 more minutes.
Turn into greased casserole dish and bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Put cheese on top and melt.

title: mom's salsa dip
directions: Dice up these ingredients: tomatoes, white onion, green onions and jalapeno pepper.
Add the juice off the tomatoes and puree in with the ingredients.
Add garlic salt and salt to your taste. Serve.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Place a layer of apples in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the sugar-cinnamon.
Cover with
remaining apples and cover with remaining sugar-cinnamon.

title: punch
directions: Freeze all day.
Just before serving, add 1 pint of ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 25.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put in the syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil, then put in the peanuts.
Stir until peanuts get light brown.
Remove from heat, then put in soda and salt.
Put on buttered Reynolds Wrap.
Let cool and break in small pieces.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Combine in order given.
Roll size of walnuts.
Flatten with fork to make round.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chicago deli egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir in mayonnaise last.
Serve on lettuce or make sandwiches.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Put in blender; whirl bananas, ice and milk until smooth.
This is low in fat and sugar.
Jerald can also have this.
It won't hurt his diabetes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Blend in Marshmallow Fluff, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve with sliced fresh fruit.

title: beer batter chicken
directions: Combine eggs and beer.
Gradually stir in flour, salt and 2 tablespoons of oil until batter is smooth.
Dip chicken into batter.
Heat oil in deep, heavy frying pan to 375°.
Add chicken and fry for 15 to 20 minutes, until chicken is golden and crisp. Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, onion and salt.
Pour over green beans and serve.

title: chocolate decorating frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
If stiff, gradually add evaporated milk to get texture you want.
Will ice 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.
Keep covered until ready to use.

title: yummy appetizers
directions: Brown and drain beef and hot sausage.
Add Accent, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Cut cheese into chunks and add to the meat mixture.
Mix until melted.
Spread on party rye.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet until bubbly (about 10 minutes).
These freeze well before or after baking.

title: my mom's oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon to mixture. Add oats and pecans. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet 7 to 10 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Makes 1 1/4 cups, equal to Eagle Brand type milk.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, place 3 cups of the lettuce; sprinkle with a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer eggs atop lettuce in bowl.
Sprinkle generously with salt.
Next, layer in order: peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise or salad dressing over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Garnish with sliced green onion and paprika, if desired.
Toss before serving.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream oleo (or butter) and sugar. Add other ingredients in order. Mix and place in an uncooked 8-inch pie crust. Cook in an oven for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 300° and continue cooking for approximately 45 minutes. Remove from oven and cool before serving. Serves 6. Can do ahead.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Add hot water to jello.
Beat cream cheese into jello.
Fold in drained, crushed pineapple.
Add 7-Up and sprinkle nuts over top.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Add water to potatoes, celery, onion, parsley, seasonings, and bouillon.
Cover and cook until tender.
Blend flour with a small amount of milk, stir into vegetable mixture.
Add rest of milk, cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: sally's spareribs
directions: Place country style spareribs in pan and sprinkle with onion salt.
(Nothing else.)
Place in oven at 450°.
Begin making sauce.

title: mushroom sherry glazed fish
directions: Stir broth and sherry into cornstarch, mixing until dissolved. Add soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Set aside.
Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Heat until bubbly, then add mushrooms. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until mushrooms are soft and liquid has accumulated in the pan.
Drain juice into cornstarch mixture.
Remove mushrooms from pan and set aside.

title: angel delite
directions: Cut angel food cake in
2 halves; chilled cake makes cutting easier.
Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Spread on layers of cake like icing.
Cut strawberries in thin slices and sprinkle over cake.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: number 1 carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and sugar all together.
Add oil, carrots, nuts, pineapple, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 75 minutes in tube pan.
May use 2 loaf pans.
Grease and flour pans.

title: pineapple cream cheese
directions: Blend pineapple into cream cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 1 cup chopped pecans.
Roll in remaining 1 cup chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with Doritos.
Next put cooked chicken.
After mixing soups and Ro-Tel together layer with this mixture.
Top with cheese.
Continue until all is used.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english tomato chutney
directions: Skin and chop tomatoes.
Cut onions into small thin rings. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt. Cover and let set overnight.
Drain off excessive liquid.
Add vinegar to almost cover mixture.
Add sugar; bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch, curry and mustard in small amount cold water.
Add to boiling mixture; cook 10 minutes. Add remaining spices.
Do not reboil.
Cover.
Refrigerate. Serve with sandwiches and burgers.
Freeze excessive chutney and thaw as needed.

title: famous divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup, water and salt in pan. Cook over medium heat until a little dropped in cold water will form a hard ball. Beat egg whites until stiff while syrup is cooking.
Pour mix into egg whites, beating continuously.
Add vanilla and beat until it loses its glossy look. Add pecans and pour onto buttered platter or drop by spoon on waxed paper. Garnish with pecan halves.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix the butter, cake mix and 1 egg.
The mixture will be very stiff.
Pat out in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the nuts over this layer.
Mix the powdered sugar, 2 eggs and the cream cheese well and pour over the nuts.
Bake at 325°
for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in large bowl.
Combine soy sauce, onion and ginger.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
Turn chicken to coat all sides.
Drain chicken and reserve sauce.
Coat chicken with cornstarch.
Place margarine in large shallow baking pan.
Put pan in hot (425°) oven until margarine is melted. Place chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake for 30 minutes or until well browned.
Turn chicken over.
Combine pineapple and juice, lemon juice and reserved sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook onion and zucchini in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough in 8 triangles and place in ungreased 10-inch pie plate.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture over crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 or 20 minutes.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into rolls about 1/2-inch in diameter and cut in 1-inch pieces.
