Put on cookie sheets and pull ends down slightly to form crescent shapes.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: hungarian pastry
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add
flour (sifted with baking powder and soda).	Add
alternately, the egg yolks with vanilla.	Beat until
thick.
Take
the
beaters
off.
Mix
well. Press dough in 11	x
17-inch
pan
with palm of hand.
Spread fruit preserves over dough.
Beat egg whites stiff with sugar; spread over the preserves.	Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together in a glass container for 24 hours, covered.
Combine 1 cup of the chopped peaches and 1/3 cup of the liquid from the glass container mixture together with the other ingredients.
Mix well and place in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate pecan balls
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Beat butter and pecans with electric mixer until well blended. Add the cookie mix, flour and water.
Beat until the mixture forms a dough.
Roll the dough into 1 inch balls and arrange on an ungreased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake 14-16 minutes or until firm.
Let cool 5 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar and set aside on a wire rack until completely cooled. Makes 5 dozen.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Roll beef in flour and brown. Add water and spices. Cover and simmer about 2 hours. I usually add leftover flour to stew. Add remaining ingredients- cook till tender, about 30 minutes.

title: rice stuffing
directions: Cook rice, celery and onion in oil in a large frypan, stir occasionally, until rice is lightly browned.

title: cold salsa
directions: Stir it all up and eat!

title: zucchini or squash casserole
directions: Slice squash or zucchini and boil in water until tender. Saute carrots and onions in oleo (4 tablespoons). Stir in 1 1/2 cups of dressing, soup and sour cream. Gently stir in squash, well drained. Put in a baking dish and spread dressing and 2 tablespoons oleo on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup of milk to well beaten egg yolks, then blend into dry ingredients. Stir until all lumps are dissolved.
Add remaining milk and mix. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then cook over low heat until desired thickness.
Add vanilla and butter.
Stir and set aside until crust is ready.
Pour into slightly baked crust.
Top with meringue and brown in 400° oven.
You can double the recipe and make 2 pies.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and season hamburger in skillet.
Drain. In separate bowl, mix Ro-Tel and both cans of soup.
In casserole dish, layer Doritos, hamburger, then soup mix.
Add a layer of shredded cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brandy-whipped cream sauce(for plum puddings, plain cake, etc.)
directions: Beat egg and add the 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon brandy or rum.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill.
Stir before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine and sour cream.
Add other ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 11-inch pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven until golden.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Add salt to taste.

title: preacher's cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chili
directions: Combine onions, green pepper and meat in skillet and cook.
Add next 4 ingredients and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally 10 minutes or until thick but still juicy.
Add beans and simmer a few minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Lay chicken flat. Place 1/2 piece of ham on top, then 1/2 piece of cheese. Roll up and wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around rolled chicken. Secure with toothpick. Place in baking pan.

title: "dreamsicle" punch
directions: Mix sherbet and ice cream.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet/ice cream and stir until ice cream is melted and punch is thick. Wonderful for wedding/showers.
One recipe makes enough to fill 2 punch bowls.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix in a large bowl in order given.
Mash, knead, squeeze and abuse dough with bare hands.
Form in small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of small glass and dip into regular sugar, then mash balls flat.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Allow cookies to cool a little on cookie sheet before removing. Put on waxed paper until completely cooled and crisp.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Select a ripe melon.
Cut in eighths and cut out fruit.
Pare green and all the pink from rind.
Cut rind in thin slices, then in strips.
Measure 7 cups.
Cover with 1 quart cold water with 3 tablespoons salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Cover with fresh water.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain again.

title: apple torte
directions: Combine apples and nuts in bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Blend dry ingredients to apple mixture. Combine eggs, margarine and vanilla in small bowl.
Mix well.
Add liquid mixture to apple mixture.
Blend until moistened.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dill veggie dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Best if put in refrigerator overnight.
Great dip for veggies, chips or crackers.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut up elephant into bite size pieces.
You may need the whole family to help you.
Add water to cover.
Add salt and pepper. Cook on top of stove on medium heat for a few weeks or until tender.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cook until done.

title: ken's cold noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles in 4 quarts boiling water until tender; cool. Mix remaining ingredients well.
Toss with noodles.
Chill before serving.

title: low-fat choco brownie bites
directions: Combine all ingredients to form a stiff batter.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet that has been coated with Pam no-stick cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 10 medium size cookies.

title: chili dip
directions: Layer in microwave-safe
dish.	Cream the cheese, chili then cheese.
Microwave	until
heated thoroughly.
Serve with dip style Fritos.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a large, greased iron skillet at 350° until well done.

title: rutabaga and apples
directions: In covered saucepan, boil rutabaga for about 20 minutes in salt water.
Drain well.
Rub sides of 2-quart casserole with butter.
Place half the rutabaga and half the apples in it. Sprinkle with half the brown sugar and dash of salt.
Repeat layers, ending with brown sugar and butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great with turkey or ham.
Serves 4.

title: biscuit burgers
directions: Brown beef and sausage with comino, Greek seasoning, garlic salt, green pepper, onion and oregano.
Spread biscuits.
Spoon on meat mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon tomato sauce.
Top with slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Spread another biscuit and cover.
Pinch edges together.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 15.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Wash all vegetables; cut broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Baste from time to time.
Drain and serve.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in condensed milk.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla until combined.
Cover each candy kiss completely with 1 level tablespoon dough.
Place cookies 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
(Cookies will appear soft and shiny.)
Cool on rack set over wax paper.
Melt white chocolate and shortening.
Drizzle over cookies.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: delicious pineapple pie
directions: Blend cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour and serve in 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: black eyed peas
directions: Drain peas and reserve juice.
Saute chopped vegetables in bacon drippings.
Add peas, Rotel and stewed tomatoes.
Cook on top of stove.
Add crumbled bacon when ready to serve.
Serve with roast and cheese grits if you like.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown off sausage and drain; reserve 2 cups cheese and several pepperoni.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb surprise
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1-inch pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Sprinkle jello and sugar over rhubarb.
Sprinkle cake mix over all. Mix melted oleo and water.
Dribble over dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions very fine and add salt. Let stand for 2 hours, then drain in colander.
Pour vinegar, sugar and pickling spice over mixture and cook for 20 minutes. Seal up tight.

title: possom pie
directions: Press 1/2 cup pecan pieces into bottom of unbaked pie shell, then bake according to directions on pie shell.
Cream sugar and cream cheese; set aside.
Mix the two puddings together with milk. Spread cream cheese mix on cooled pie shell, then spread pudding and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remainder 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Heat together vinegar, celery seed, nutmeg, turmeric, pepper and cornstarch.
Grind together zucchini, onions and peppers. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup salt and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Then rinse in cold water and drain.
Add to hot solution and simmer (do not boil) for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars, seal and water bath for 5 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Add milk to fill can to mark.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Add dressing and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
13 servings.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onions.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan. Layer cheese and sour cream.
Top with rolls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Mix jello with 2 cups hot water and then add 1/2 cup pineapple juice and 1/2 cup apricot juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the pineapple and apricots, mashed and mixed.
Add layer of marshmallows on top of jello mixture.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: old-time fudge
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil.
Set aside.

title: sausage roll
directions: Prepare hot roll mix.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Cook onion and sausage together.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients. Let cool.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread mixture on dough. Roll up and pinch ends.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter when almost done.
Slice when cool.

title: marshmallow treats(for big and little kids)
directions: You also need 1 large pot.

title: cheesy chive potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl, mixing gently.
Spoon mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sandies butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla and mix well.
Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill for 4 hours.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and while still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture. Stir well.
Add flour, nuts, dates and raisins and stir well again.
Pour into 2 (2-quart) greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (touch test same as for cakes).

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Turn off oven and place cookies inside.
Leave cookies in oven for 2 hours or overnight.

title: layered cheese mold
directions: Combine cream cheese and Roquefort in food processor.
Pulse until smooth.
Combine basil, parsley, spinach, garlic and olive oil.
Pulse in processor until paste. Add pecans and Romano cheese to basil mixture. Mix olives and tomatoes.

title: venison jerky
directions: Slice meat into 3/8-inch strips.
In a bowl, combine all ingredients, except meat.
Stir well to dissolve all soluble ingredients.
Place strips of meat in marinade, be sure they are completely submerged.
Marinate overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Divide into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Heat oil in large, heavy skillet or wok. Add beef; cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper, celery, beans, tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; stir well.
Add macaroni.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Stir often. Add a little water, if necessary to keep from sticking.
Stir in olives and serve.
Serves 6.

title: valentine's day salad
directions: Dissolve candies in water.
Add to Jell-O, stirring to dissolve.
Chill to egg white consistency.
Add applesauce. Chill until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter and cool.
Add graham cracker crumbs and half of pecans.
Mix well and pat out in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until brown; let cool.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; spoon into a small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: mountain pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Melt butter in 2-qt. casserole dish in oven.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour pie filling on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: rolled molasses cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll thin.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: candy nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar gradually and then margarine.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: diet jello cake
directions: Cut and peel the apples.
Place in 1-quart microwave-safe dish.
Add Jell-O and Knox.
Add 2 cups hot water.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Microwave 10 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: ambrosia salad platter
directions: Peel and slice oranges.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice on the slices and store, covered, in this refrigerator.
Just before serving, drain the pineapple and cherries (or wash and hull strawberries).
Use a large platter to arrange a layer of orange slices, then a layer of pineapple slices.
Sprinkle coconut to taste over all.
Spoon a dollop of Cool Whip into the center of each pineapple slice and top each with a cherry or strawberry.

title: sourdough from starter to table
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
Stir in warm water.
Cover with plastic wrap; cut 4 or 5 small holes with a sharp knife.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.
Remove starter from refrigerator; let starter stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Stir well.
Remove 1 cup starter; use in a recipe or give to a friend. Prepare 1 recipe Starter Food and stir into remaining starter; let stand, uncovered, 8 to 12 hours.
Cover with plastic wrap; cut 4 or 5 holes in wrap.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.
Repeat 3 times.
Use all or discard after 4 feedings.

title: bread and butter zucchini pickles
directions: Put vinegar, sugar, salt and seed in large, heavy pot over high heat and bring to boil.
Add zucchini and onions and cover. Remove from heat and let stand for 1 hour.
Return pot to stove over high heat.
Bring to boil again, reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Pack pickles loosely in 4 sterilized 1-quart jars.
Pour liquid to cover and scald.
Process jars in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
When cool, store in dark, cool place.

title: green layered salad
directions: Mix in order given. Chunked or sliced tomatoes can be put on top.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and let cool.
Add egg.
Add yeast to cold water for 5 minutes; add to above.
Add flour and mix.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
About 3 hours before needed, roll dough on floured board and cut.
Place on pans or muffin tins.
Raise 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: saucy brussels sprouts
directions: Wash and trim sprouts; cut large ones in half.
In a saucepan, cook sprouts, covered with a small amount of water for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, brown sugar, salt and dry mustard until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Blend in sour cream and gently heat with Brussels sprouts added.
Do not allow the sauce to boil again.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Stir in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Stir half the flour mixture into the shortening mixture. Beat in 2 Tbsp. of the hot water. Stir in remaining flour mixture, then the remaining water, beating after each addition. Stir in diced apples and nuts. Spread in two greased 9x9 inch pans or 1 9x13 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes or until sides pull away from pan.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: red deviled ham balls
directions: Mix cream cheese and deviled ham. Chill until firm. Form into bite size balls and roll in paprika, then in chopped nuts. Serve on toothpicks. Makes 40.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 can of onions on top of casserole before serving.

title: family style beef brisket dinner
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish, add onion soup mix, blended with water.
Add brisket, turning to coat with soup mixture.
Loosely wrap with foil and roast 1 hour.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Coat well with soup mixture.
Reset foil and continue roasting 2 hours or until brisket and veggies are tender. Thicken gravy, if desired.

title: irish cabbage soup
directions: In a large pan, brown the turkey.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: dessert - fun no work cobbler
directions: Pour can of cherry pie filling (or can use peach filling) into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle over this 1 box of cake mix (only dry mixture).
Drizzle over this butter and sprinkle nuts on top of this.
Press lightly down into cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 large or 9 medium servings.

title: kahlua marbled pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine gingersnaps and graham cracker crumbs with powdered sugar and butter.
Press into 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Blend instant pudding and milk.
Spread over last layer.
Then spread the other half of Cool Whip over that and sprinkle with finely ground nuts or grated chocolate bar.
You may substitute any instant pudding.
For lemon, add 2 tablespoons lemon juice with pudding mixture.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Combine ingredients. Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Top with sliced peaches (treat the peaches with Fruit Fresh to preserve color), then with whipped cream.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix and keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican dipper
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Blend cheeses in crock-pot with tomato sauce.
Add beef and onion mixture; blend in mushrooms.
Serve warm with nachos or taco chips.

title: happy camper trail mix
directions: Stir all contents together in a large bowl.
Enjoy! Yield: Approximately 3-quarts (4 to 6 campers for a weekend).

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla flavoring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 4 hours to firm. Top with desired pie filling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Combine sugar, reserved juice, eggs and flour. Cook until a custard-like sauce. Fold into the rosamarina and let set overnight.
Next day fold in fruit and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Marshmallows and maraschino cherries are optional.

title: catfish poblano
directions: Start rice cooking.
Dice scallions, tomatoes, potato and celery.
Heat olive oil; divide between 2 pans.
Crush garlic in press.
Add garlic to heated oil in one pan and saute 30 seconds. Add butter and diced vegetables to pan.
Heat olive oil in second pan and add crushed garlic; saute.
Add fish steaks to second pan.
Saute fish steaks adding peppercorns, cilantro, cayenne pepper and white pepper.

title: salmon fluff
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon in deep oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: arabian pork chops
directions: Brown the chops on both sides in a skillet.
Place in a shallow casserole.
Arrange slices of onions and tomatoes on each chop and sprinkle on green peppers.
Put salt and water in the skillet and heat, making brown gravy.
Pour over chops.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and fry. Pour grease off. Mix soup, milk, sausage, green pepper and pimentos with noodles. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smothered apples
directions: Combine in a large pan. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the pie filling, sugar and water. Add other ingredients.
Pour into mold or pan.
Chill until set.

title: rolled stuffed meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, salt and pepper thoroughly on waxed paper; roll meat mixture out into 1/2-inch thick rectangle (about 8 x 11-inch).
Lay ham crosswise, then cheese.
Sprinkle with chopped olives.
Roll meat like a jellyroll.
Secure the ends and seam by pinching them together.
Place seam side down in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake on High in microwave for 5 minutes, then Medium power for 16 minutes, then on Medium-low for 4 minutes.

title: seven-layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a large platter.
Layer, in order, the lettuce, olives, cheese, peppers, sour cream, tomatoes and onions.
Drizzle salsa over top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake for about 45 minutes.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Chop potatoes, onions, celery, green pepper and eggs. Mix together. Mix dressing, mayonnaise, mustard and relish; stir into vegetable mixture.

title: maryland shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat soup.
Add cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; place in mold.
Let set.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cook onion in oleo until tender but not brown; about 20 minutes.
Add beef broth, sherry, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; bring to a boil.
Pour into 6 individual casseroles or ovenproof bowls.
Float a slice of bread in each; sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Top with a slice of Provolone cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes or broil until cheese is bubbly (about 5 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake according to recipe on box and bake.
Let cake cool completely.
Mix jello.
Put holes in cake with a large fork, then pour entire jello mix over cake.
Let cake set for awhile to absorb jello.
Very tasty cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: paul's venison stew
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Save grease and set aside bacon.
Shake meat in flour and fry in bacon grease just to brown.
Add meat, seasonings and vegetables to large pot and simmer for 2 hours. Might have to add a little water.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: In skillet brown beef, sausage, onion and oregano until done. Pour
off
fat.
Add soups and water;
simmer until all is	heated through.
Pour into 2 quart baking dish:
noodles, then
meat. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Place in oven at 400° until cheese is melted or until hot.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and yogurt in a serving bowl.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir hamburger in skillet.
Remove from heat; drain. Stir in onion, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cover and reserve.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Pour into pie pan.
Dip each tortilla into sauce.
Coat both sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup hamburger mix into each tortilla and roll up. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas and bake uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes. Garnish with cheese, sour cream, onions and lime wedges.

title: devilicious game ball
directions: In a bowl combine all ingredients except pecans.
Shape mixture like a football.
Chill.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Add pimento or string cheese for decoration.
Serve with crackers. Makes one (2-cup) cheese ball.

title: superb chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add melted margarine.
In another bowl, beat the egg yolks and 1 egg; add milk and vanilla.
Combine the two mixtures.
Pour into a 10-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° until custard sets.
Cover with meringue made from remaining egg whites.
Sprinkle additional sugar on top of meringue until it is well coated.
Bake at 325° until it is golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes in bottom of a buttered Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle with onion, flour, salt and pepper; then dot layer with butter.
Repeat layers until all potatoes are used.
Pour canned milk over top; rinse can if more fluid is needed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: garden casserole
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon melted butter into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Coat surface.
Layer vegetables in dish.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and cornstarch to tomatoes and pour over vegetables. Drizzle with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: zwieback(german rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with sugar.
Mix together scalded milk, salt, instant potatoes and melted margarine.
Add yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour, approximately 5 cups.
Knead.
Let rise until double.
Pinch off small balls of dough, placing on greased baking sheet.
Let rise, then stack to make "double buns".
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan drops
directions: Chop pecans coarsely.
Cream butter and shortening together. Beat in sugar.
Stir in flour.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: pasta slaw
directions: Cook pasta according to label directions; drain, rinse and drain again.
Combine cole slaw dressing, onion and mustard; add pasta, stirring to coat.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least one hour.
Just before serving, add cabbage, green pepper and carrots to pasta mixture, stirring to coat.
Makes ten 1/2 cup servings.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high beat, brown chicken in butter.
Add Pasta Accents and water.
Stir to combine.
Cover and reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp and tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Take out stems and dice.
Mix together: mushroom stems, crumbled bread, garlic powder, onion and parsley. Melt butter and pour over mixture until moistened.
You may need to add more butter.
Fill mushrooms by teaspoonful of mix.
Put mushrooms on a cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until stuffing looks browned.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix hot water in jello.
Let stand until it begins to set. Mix in lemon juice, sugar and cream cheese.
Whip milk until stiff then mix in all ingredients.

title: ten men dip
directions: On a large round or oval platter or plate, layer dip in the order listed above, except cheese.
Let chill in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours and then add grated cheese right before serving. Serve with taco chips.

title: hungarian nut roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Combine the rest of the ingredients. Add yeast and milk mixture, blending very well.
Divide dough into 4 or 5 parts, depending on length of nut roll wanted.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with nut filling; roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Let rise for 1 hour or until double in size.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 4 large rolls, cookie sheet length.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco casserole very large recipe
directions: Brown hamburger.
When brown, drain.
In a bowl, microwave Cheddar cheese soup, cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crushed tortilla chips or Doritos.
Put 1/2 of soup mixture over top of chips.
Place all of ground beef over soup mixture, then all soup mixture over hamburger.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cover top of casserole with more crushed chips and shredded cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: party piquant meat balls
directions: Mix above and shape into size of walnuts.
Brown in oven.
In slow cooker, add meat balls to sauce.
Serve for party time or any added meal.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice.
Cook onion in a small amount of margarine until clear.
Add ground beef and brown. Drain.
Add mustard and ketchup.

title: barbecued beef and pork burgers
directions: Tie pickling spice in a cheesecloth bag.
Place beef, pork, onions, water and pickling spice in a heavy Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 6 hours or until very tender.
Drain liquid.
Vigorously stir meat with a meat fork until shredded.
Stir in ketchup and vinegar; simmer an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheesy fruit-n-nut salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; toss gently. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add to apple mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: honey lime fruit salad
directions: Prepare Honey Lime Dressing; cool slightly.
Pour over fruit in bowl.
Toss until fruit is glazed.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next six ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick (45 minutes to 1 hour), stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water (salted) until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with next five ingredients.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar and pineapple juice. Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partly set.
Add apples, oranges, cranberries, pineapples and walnuts.
Chill until set.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and remove pulp. Steam peppers in 1 inch of water for 5 minutes, cool. Add Spanish rice and catsup to cooked ground beef. Spoon mixture into peppers. Place in baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: light cream cheese frosting
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the cream cheese, marshmallow crme, lemon juice and vanilla until well combined.
Then gradually beat in the powdered sugar.
Marshmallow crme replaces the butter in this super-easy frosting.
To keep things neat and simplify cleanup, coat the measuring cup with no-stick spray before measuring the marshmallow crme.
Calories, fat, and cholesterol were also reduced by replacing regular cream cheese with light cream cheese.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk using a wire whip (do not beat). Fold in sour cream and 1/2 container of Cool Whip. Layer in casserole the wafers, pudding mixture and bananas; repeat, then top with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream
margarine, sugar and cocoa; add eggs and vanilla; mix. Add
flour,
nuts
and
salt;
beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased 9
x 10-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream on hot cake and cool.
Melt 1 stick of margarine; add milk
and vanilla.
Stir in powdered sugar and cocoa until smooth.
Spread on top of marshmallow cream.
May be sprinkled with more chopped pecans, if desired.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend with a fork; then flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Shape into balls ready for rolling.
Wrap each in wax paper and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
When ready to use, lightly flour both sides and roll out.
Can be frozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump then spread pineapple into it.
Spread fruit pie filling on top of pineapple layer. Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Cut margarine into pats and place evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes (for crunchy top), 60 minutes (for regular top).
Serve with Cool Whip.
Can use blueberry pie filling.

title: soda cracker bars
directions: Grease jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Line with saltines. Melt butter and brown sugar together in a saucepan.
Stir and boil for three minutes, blending well.
Spread over saltines and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chopped candy bars over top when slightly cooled.
(Can be spread when chocolate is melted.)
Cut between crackers when cooled.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mash squash and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie crust as directed and cool.
Smooth peanut butter over crust.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed; fold in 1/4 cup chips and pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip and chips.

title: egyptian rice
directions: Brown ground meat and onions together.
Drain fat; add salt (not much, the soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce contain a lot of salt) and pepper to taste, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, consomme and uncooked rice.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Add mushrooms and slivered almonds; return to heat until last 2 ingredients have been heated through.

title: hot chocolate sauce(delicious)
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Stir while boiling.
Immediately pour over pound cake, angel food cake or your favorite plain cake.
Put this on individual servings.
The men love this!

title: cheese cake
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Mix cheese with pudding, milk and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla buttercream frosting
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, milk and vanilla with electric mixer on low speed until well blended and smooth.
If frosting becomes too thick, beat in additional milk by teaspoonfuls until spreading consistency.

title: walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, follow package directions.
Drain and place in flat greased dish (2-quart).
Melt butter in flour; cook over low heat.
Add chicken stock base.
Gradually add 2 cups milk.
Cook until thickened, pour over broccoli.
Heat water and 6 tablespoons butter until melted.
Pour over stuffing mix and toss. Add nuts over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine the bay leaves, salt, ground red pepper, black and white pepper, ground cumin and ground nutmeg.
Mix these ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press mixture into dish and top with crushed potato chips or corn flakes.
Drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger cheese macaroni with manwich
directions: Brown hamburger 30 minutes.
Drain grease.
Cook noodles until done, 30 minutes.
Drain.
Add Hamburger Helper cheeseburger macaroni.
Cook according to recipe.
Add ingredients together, then add Manwich and cheese from Hamburger Helper package.
Mix together on low for 30 minutes, stirring constantly; turn off to cook.

title: life saver chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, together. Put chicken in baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave on High for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in 4 small loaf pans at 350° until done (approximately 30 minutes).

title: honey-pecan biscuits
directions: Combine honey and cinnamon; divide into 10 greased muffin cups.
Arrange 3 pecan halves in each cup.
Top with 1 biscuit. Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.

title: cold tomato-cucumber soup
directions: Season tomato juice (V-8 can be used) to taste with a good French dressing made with olive oil.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in large soup plates.
Pass croutons and diced cucumbers; add these to soup.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Fold in cooked broccoli. Grease a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish and layer half of the dressing in the bottom of dish.
Cover with soup, sour cream and broccoli mixture. Top with remaining dressing.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry steak
directions: Marinate the meat 1/2 hour or longer in mixture of soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch, sugar and pepper.
Get frypan hot, almost smoking, then add 2 tablespoons of olive oil and vegetables; stir-fry until just transparent (about 2 minutes).
Take up.
Wipe or clean skillet and reheat.
Add about 2 tablespoons of oil, then add meat and stir-fry until almost done.
Add vegetables and remainder of marinade.
Stir until well heated.
Serve immediately over fluffy rice.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and rum flavoring. Stir in flour, cherries and pecans.
Form dough into 2 (8-inch) rolls.
Roll dough in shredded coconut to coat.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes 60 cookies (approximately).
Great holiday cookie!

title: garden relish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over veggies; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Yields about 1 quart.

title: sausage-cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil and stir in grits.
Return to boil, cover and cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups sharp cheese, milk, oleo, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Stir until all melts.
Stir small amount of grits into beaten egg.
Add to remaining grits mixture, stirring constantly. Spoon half of grits into 8-inch greased dish.
Top with sausage. Spoon remaining grits over sausage, cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Bring to room temperature and bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: sausage and eggs souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Crumble in bowl.
Beat eggs, add milk, mustard and bread.
Stir; add cheese and sausage.
Spoon into 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
May refrigerate overnight. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and dates.
Microwave on High, 3 1/2 to 6 minutes or until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Add nuts and/or coconut and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: sliced cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar, then add slightly beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda, making a soft dough. If dough is too sticky, add more flour till easy to roll.
Then make long rolls and lay on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let cool, then ice with any light icing and slice as you like.

title: fish for two
directions: Place fish fillets in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour melted butter and lemon juice over fish.
Sprinkle lemon pepper seasoning and next 4 ingredients evenly over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes or until fish is lightly browned and flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Garnish if desired.
Yields 2 servings.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Combine white and rye flours in a large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of flour mixtures, salt, bran cereal, cornmeal and dry yeast; mix well.
In a large saucepan, combine water, molasses, chocolate, and butter/margarine.
Heat over low heat until liquid is very warm (120-130 F).
The butter and chocolate do not have to be completely melted.
Gradually add liquid ingredients to dry and beat 2 minutes with an electric mixer at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add potatoes and 1 cup flour mixture.
Beat at high for 12 minutes, scraping bowl.
Stir in caraway seed and enough additional flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 15 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover with a clean towel and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hr.
Punch down and turn onto lightly floured board.
Divide dough in half and shape each half into a round ball.
Place shaped dough in two 8-inch round cake pans which have been greased.
Cover with a clean towel and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, approx. 45 minutes. Bake breads at 350 F about 50 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped with knuckles.
Remove bread from pans to cooling racks.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, nuts and other ingredients, except confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Pinch off small bits and roll into finger shape pieces.
Bake in very slow oven (300°).
Do not brown.
When done, remove and roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over roast; cook 1 1/2 hours. Slice thin and return to cook until good and tender.
Serve on rolls and reserve broth for dipping.

title: supreme chicken
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Add all ingredients, except paprika and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add cheese on top.
Serves 12.

title: mulled cider for a crowd
directions: Pour the apple cider into a large party size electric coffee maker.
Place the mulling spices in the basket.
Plug in and perk! When the red light goes on, you have delicious, hot mulled cider. Serve with a cinnamon stick.
Serves 10 to 15.

directions: Butter	2
baking sheets and keep warm.
Combine baking soda, 1

water	and vanilla and set aside.
Combine sugar, 1 cup

corn syrup in large saucepan.

title: texas cake
directions: Melt together cocoa, butter and water.
Add flour, eggs, sugar and sour cream to chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake about 8 potatoes.
Cool and slice.
Put remaining ingredients (except green onions) in saucepan and heat until hot, stirring constantly.
Put potatoes in greased dish.
Cut up onions on top of potatoes.
Pour cheese mixture on potatoes.
Bake until it bubbles, 350°.

title: best ever slush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in an empty ice cream pail.
Mix well and freeze.
Take out of freezer 4 to 5 hours ahead to thaw a little. Chop with a knife to make slush.
Put into punch bowl and add ginger ale just before serving; will be slushy.
Makes 50 (5 ounce) servings.
(You can make this several days ahead of time and keep frozen until ready to use.
Take out a few hours ahead of time.)

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll thin and cut in narrow strips.
Bake in slow oven at 275° until light brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, add cornbread mix last.
Pour into an 11 x 13 greased dish.
Bake about 25 minutes at 400°.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: original recipe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes, until firm.
Makes one 9 to 10-inch pie.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Put cranberry and pineapple juice in 30-cup coffee maker; fill to 30-cup marker with water.
Put sugar, cloves, cinnamon and salt in coffee basket.
Perk through cycle.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 30.

title: ruth's baked beans
directions: Spray Pam in skillet and heat on stove.
Scramble and brown meat.
Mix onion and bell pepper in a teaspoon or two of margarine.
In mixing bowl, mix together browned, drained meat, beans with their liquid, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Pour or ladle into a bean pot and bake slowly at 325° in oven for 2 to 3 hours, covered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball and wrap remaining beef slices around ball.
Chill.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain well.
Peel and slice potatoes and carrots.
Mix in a 2-quart casserole dish: meat, vegetables, soup and milk.
Season to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian chop suey(serves 6)
directions: Saute beef in pan until it loses its pink color (add a little oil, if needed, to prevent sticking), then add sliced vegetables and continue cooking 5 or 10 minutes.
Add tomato paste, plus 2 or 3 cans of water and the soy sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Cook shells; drain, then add to sauce mixture and serve.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt margarine in hot milk.
Pour over bread crumbs. Mix well and add to squash. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in eggs and pour into greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake about 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: chocolate covered peanut balls
directions: Melt margarine; stir in peanut butter and powdered sugar. Mix well.
Add graham crackers, coconut and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin in a double boiler. Dip balls into mixture and set on wax paper to cool.

title: pecan soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Cut in margarine/butter.
Stir in pecans and currants.
Stir in eggs and enough buttermilk/sour milk to make soft dough.
Knead on floured board until smooth, about 1 minute. Shape into ball and place on greased baking sheet. Flatten to a 6-inch diameter.
Cut a deep "X" into top of loaf.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: butterscotch bread
directions: Divide rolls for 2 layers.
Layer first: frozen bread, 1 stick butter and 1 package pudding.
Repeat.
Let rise all night.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients with light Miracle Whip.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: jackie's pretzel salad
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan the pretzels, sugar and melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Follow directions of pancake batter, as if you were to make pancakes.
Then add corn, pepper, salt and egg.
Mix together. Drop by rounded tablespoonful size into hot oil and fry.

title: italian chicken
directions: Pour bottle of dressing into medium size bowl.
Salt, pepper and garlic salt the chicken.
Let chicken marinate for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Mix wafers and 2 sticks butter.
Put 1/2 mixture on bottom; place ice cream (cut in half), then other 1/2 of wafer mixture. Cover with sauce.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon into large bowl.
Add oil, apples and vanilla.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Beat eggs until light yellow in color.
Gradually add sugar; continue beating until light and fluffy.
Fold egg mixture into apple mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.

title: chicken papaya
directions: Cut papaya and set aside.
Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces. Peel and chop ginger and garlic.
Add oil into frying pan and brown garlic; then add ginger and chicken.
Saute for 20 minutes; add salt.
Add 4 cups of water, boil and simmer until chicken is done, about 1/2 hour (1 to 1 1/2 hours if using stewing chicken).
Add papaya and continue to cook for about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream butter.
Add vanilla, sugar and salt.
Keep beating as you add the water.
Then add flour.
Finally mix in almonds. Chill dough and then roll into crescent shapes.
Should look like good sized whole shrimp.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until very light brown.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar or put some powdered sugar in a sieve and shake it over the cookies.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter
and cheese together.
Add dry ingredients which have been
sifted
together.
Add
water and mix and end with more dry mixture.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: deer meat balls
directions: Combine meat, onion, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 1-inch balls, placing a small amount of cream cheese into center of each meat ball.
Brown in a small amount of fat.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and remaining cream cheese.
Cook slow in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Add sour cream before serving. Serves 8.

title: english walnut pie
directions: Mix all together, put in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in loaf pan.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chili con queso
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients; simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add cheese, simmer for 30 minutes longer.
Fry ground beef; drain.
Add to cheese mixture.
Serve as dip with Fritos or tortillas.
Yield: 25 to 50 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Grate and melt cheese in double boiler.
Then add all other ingredients and stir for 15 minutes.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in large ziploc bag. Marinate 4 hours.
Grill 3-4 minutes on each side.
Baste often.

title: brownie trifle cake(club member: terah smith)
directions: Bake brownie mix; cool and crumble half of brownies in a bowl. Pour syrup over this. Add Cool Whip, then put remaining brownies over this, then syrup, then Cool Whip and drizzle topping over all. You can use cherries and nuts on top, then drizzle topping over if you want.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks and add the cup of sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Cook to thick custard. Roll graham crackers to crush them.

Melt butter and brown sugar, then add to cracker crumbs. Spread 1/2 cup of crumbs in baking dish. Add custard. Beat egg whites, 1 teaspoon sugar and baking powder; spread over custard. Add rest of crumbs.
Bake until egg whites are brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken and cashews
directions: Combine honey, oil, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cut up chicken breasts into bite size pieces and marinate in the honey mixture while you are chopping vegetables.
Fry crushed garlic clove in 2 tablespoons oil in a wok.
Remove garlic and add chicken mixture. Cook through.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/4 cup water.
When chicken is cooked, add water with bouillon and then add all of the vegetables (you may make substitutions).
Cook for 3 minutes, until vegetables are brightly colored and still a little crispy.
Add cashews and cook for 1 more minute.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: golden cauliflower
directions: Put cauliflower in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Set aside and melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add the flour and stir until blended over low heat.
If you burn it, start over.
Slowly add milk and stir until thick and even.
Add rest, except bread crumbs and cheese.
Put cauliflower in baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Place potato slices on a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil; cover with onion slices.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon; dot with butter.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Cook about 1 hour on grill.
Turn several times. Serves 6.

title: coffee can bread
directions: You will need 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: fruits fantasia
directions: In a blender, process the first 4 ingredients on low speed until smooth.
Using a melon baller, cut cantaloupe into small balls.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Top with yogurt mixture; garnish with mint sprigs.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello with 2 cups boiling water and 1 cup cold water. Mix with rest of ingredients and dump into glass baking dish. Refrigerate to gel and top with Cool Whip.

title: stir fry shrimp
directions: Wash the shrimp, remove the shell and devein. Chop the broccoli and discard the large stem. Chop the peppers, mushrooms, and onion. In a large pan, or wok, pour 1 tbsp. of olive oil, and add shrimp. Saute shrimp for 2 minutes, then add broccoli, and mix well. Add green peppers, 1/2 tsp. salt, and pepper to your liking.

title: blueberry poppy seed brunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add lemon peel and egg.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add dry ingredients.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
After baked, sprinkle with sugar.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Boil milk and sugars to boil stage (240°).
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to stick to sides of saucepan, then pour into patties.
Make only one recipe at a time because it hardens as you get finished.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Put ingredients in order in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all together; heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Take mixture and spread in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces (makes about 4 dozen).

title: muffin pan snacks
directions: Pour gelatin into bowl. Add 1 cup boiling water to gelatin. Stir with rubber scraper until gelatin is completely dissolved. Add 1 cup of cold water.

title: apple or pear crisp
directions: Toss apples or pears with 1 tablespoon flour in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Add concentrated apple juice.
Coat well.
In small bowl, combine the rest of the flour and the spices with the margarine and mix until well blended.
Gradually stir in the graham cracker crumbs until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over the fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes until the topping is lightly browned and the fruit is tender.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares (1 square = 1 fruit equivalent).

title: sno-ball cake
directions: Pinch cake into small pieces.
Put half in large bowl; set aside.
Mix jello according to directions on box and add 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator for about 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove and add drained pineapple; pour over 1/2 cake pieces.
Add rest of cake pieces.
Pour in rest of jello mixture. Put in freezer for about 1 hour.
Take out of freezer and set bowl in a pan of warm water for a few seconds.
Slide cake onto cake plate.
Spread the other tub of Cool Whip over the cake, then place cherries on cake.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Mix last four ingredients and spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange rolls(similar to the club recipe)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough; mix well.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease the top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) until double in bulk.

title: butternut squash, orange and ginger soup
directions: Peel and remove seeds from squash.
Chop and boil in chicken broth until tender.
Blend.
Return to stove; add other ingredients and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: fruited cream cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple and strawberries, stirring until blended.
Serve with bagels or gingersnaps.

title: tomato salad
directions: Place tomatoes and chopped onion in salad bowl and use just enough oil to coat salad. Sprinkle with oregano. Serves 4.

title: baked omelette
directions: Fry meat and drain well. Beat eggs slightly. Add all ingredients to the egg
mixture and mix well. Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan and cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 8 adults.

title: three minute pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell (9-inch).
Bake for 45 minutes at 250°.
Cool and serve.

title: pineapple crunch
directions: Mix together butter and bread cubes until butter is absorbed. Set aside in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs well, then beat in sugar. Stir in undrained pineapple.
Place in baking dish.
Spread cubes on top.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Good with ham.

title: smoked salmon squares
directions: Toast bread; trim crusts.
Spread bread with cream cheese. Cut each piece into quarters.
Cut salmon slices to fit on top of toast.
Top toast with slices.
Garnish with strips of lemon peel.

title: baked chicken with celery salt
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly and pat dry.
Coat with pepper to taste.
Insert garlic in cavity along with fresh herbs; sage and thyme are good as well as basil.
Coat chicken with lots of celery salt until you have a thick coating.
Bake at 375° until done. Celery salt makes a juicy chicken with a crisp crust.

title: stir and drop donuts
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. In a separate bowl, add milk and oil; mix.
Combine the 2 bowls with egg.
Heat 3 cups of oil.
Spoon dough out in tablespoonfuls and drop in oil for 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Take out of pan; let cool and dip in powdered sugar or cinnamon-sugar.

title: rhonda's salad
directions: Mix lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon together.
Mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and sugar together.
Pour dressing on right before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, beating well.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to first three.
Add chopped dates and pecans.
Grease five 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill half full; it will take all to do that.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli, Minute rice, 3/4 jar Cheez Whiz, 1 can cream of mushroom soup and onions; mix well. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Cream until fluffy. Add flour with salt and blend in mixture well.
Add pecans and continue mixing until well blended and holds together.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 20 minutes until begins to brown on bottom.
Do not brown completely.
Cool on paper towels and roll in powdered sugar. Store in container with tight lid.

title: maxine's christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add Jell-O to dissolve.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and gradually add Jell-O.
Blend in all other ingredients and fold in whipped cream. Pour into a 6-cup mold or dish and chill.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: deer roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in large baking dish or slow cooker. Cook 3 to 4 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve with side dish of noodles and fresh rolls.

title: pasta with scallops and lemon mustard butter
directions: Bring wine and lemon peel to simmer in heavy skillet.
Add scallops and cook until opaque, 60 to 90 seconds, using slotted spoon to transfer scallops to bowl.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain off most of the fat.
Add flour and stir well.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Serve over biscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Mix butter and peanut butter, then add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well together with eggs.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from a spoon onto cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
For a softer cookie, bake only for about 8 minutes (they will be only starting to set up, but will firm as they cool).
Let cool and store in an airtight container. Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator for 4 days. Remove from refrigerator on the fourth day and mix well again.
On the fifth day, remove from the refrigerator and make into 5 rolls. Place on baking sheet and bake for 10 hours at 180°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake as directed on 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Cool. Beat cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread over cooled cake, then spread drained pineapple over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef until crumbly.
Drain.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle meat with garlic salt.
Next, layer the sliced raw onions over meat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Fill remainder of dish with sliced raw potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour creamed corn over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes (until potatoes are done).

title: helen's tuna casserole(low-fat recipe)
directions: Boil noodles and drain. Saute onion in minimum amount of oil. Add soup, milk, tuna, salt and pepper. Add to noodles and green peas. Place in a large casserole dish. Cut cheese into triangles and place on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown, drain and rinse sausage.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 2-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cherry bits
directions: Over slow heat, melt ingredients.
Put 1/2 teaspoon on top of each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan melt morsels and margarine. Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press 1/2 mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in condensed milk, vanilla and egg. Mix well. Pour into dish. Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and cream.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and evaporated milk.
Add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, carrot and celery just to tender.
Remove broccoli and set aside.
Add milk to broccoli.
Salt and thicken with 4 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Put cut up broccoli back in soup.

title: giant gingerbread kids
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, molasses and water in a large bowl on low speed until blended.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled, 1 to 2 hours.
Heat the oven to 375°.
Sprinkle a pastry sheet lightly with flour.
Turn dough onto surface.
Roll dough with a rolling pin until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a 5 to 8-inch gingerbread kid cutter.
Lift cookies carefully with a large spatula onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cookies cool 3 minutes, then carefully remove from cookie sheet with a spatula.
Cool and decorated with frosting, if desired.

title: bud's favorite salad dressing
directions: Prepare dressing in advance.
(I use a mixer.)
Store in a jar.
Use on spinach salad or green salad.

title: tomato-okra casserole
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add okra; cook until tender. Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese, then cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter over medium heat.
Gradually stir in cheese and then cream. Continue heating sauce just to boiling point.
Be careful not to continue boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add parsley.
Add sauce to pasta and toss.
Serves 6.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of the uncooked noodles in a 13 x 9-inch pan; spread 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture over; add 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves 12.

title: cherry dream dessert
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and powdered sugar with mixer. Add vanilla.
Whip Dream Whip as directed on box and mix with first mixture.
Line pie pan with crushed Ritz crackers and spread first mixture on crackers.
Top with cherry or strawberry pie mix.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Years ago,
a Kentucky grandmother gave a new bride this following "receet" for washing clothes.
It appears below just as it is written and despite the spelling, has a bit of philosophy:

title: low-fat alfredo sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over hot fettucine noodles.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend
together
margarine
and cheese.
Then gradually add flour,
salt and pepper; form into rolls and cut into thin slices on
ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Place pecan half on each slice if desired.
Cook at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread dough; divide in half.
Roll out and let rise. Spread sausage (cooked or uncooked) and cheeses on dough.
Stir egg and drizzle on top of cheeses.
Roll up, put in 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° until done.

title: noodles with spinach and peppers
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
In large skillet, over medium-high heat, add oil, onion and garlic.
Saute 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in pepper strips.
Saute 5 more minutes.
Stir in spinach; cook, stirring constantly, until just wilted.
Add pasta and Parmesan cheese.
Add salt and pepper and toss until heated. Serves 4.

title: hamburger boats
directions: Fry and season hamburger with salt and pepper; drain.
Add mushroom soup and sour cream.
Open hot dog buns, but do not pull apart.
Fill with hot hamburger mixture.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut or break cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces. Mix together the Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well and pour over broccoli and cauliflower.
Stir to coat broccoli and cauliflower.
Last, add grated cheese and bacon bits.
Let sit in refrigerator a couple of hours before serving.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain juice from beets.
Place in saucepan.
Add sugar and vinegar; boil vigorously.
Slice beets; add onions, cloves, salt and pepper.
Pour juice over beets and let stand.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in Corning Ware dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Arrange pineapple slices over sugar. Garnish with cherries.
Set aside.

title: mcfarlain's barnyard chicken salad
directions: Toss and chill before serving.

title: apple cake delight
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Stir with a spoon.
Spread into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.

title: dilly shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and rinse in cold watter.
Chop shrimp. Gradually blend milk and mayonnaise into cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add onion, salt, dill and shrimp.
Turn into serving dish and chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package.
Bake in long pan.
Cook pineapple with sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over hot cake.
Mix instant pudding and pour over sliced bananas on the cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with coconut and pecans.
Serve in squares.

title: pig-pickin' cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in 3 large pans for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In skillet, mix beef, taco or chili powder, tomato sauce, corn, onion and green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: lasagna sauce
directions: The longer it's cooked the better.
Cook lasagna noodles until tender.
Add 1 teaspoon oil.
When tender, drain noodles and rinse in cold water (will keep from sticking together).
Put layer of sauce, layer of Mozzarella cheese, then layer of noodles.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: vegetable chicken
directions: Slice celery and carrots into thin strips.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lucy's meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put foil on for first 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in steamer or boil until tender but not overdone; drain water if boiled.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight, at least.
The longer it sits the more the flavor goes through the carrots.
Keep in refrigerator several weeks.
Serve cold.
If you like onions add a small chopped onion to the mixture.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix cake mix per instructions and pour over coconut and nuts.

title: eagle brand bars
directions: Chocolate Mixture:
Cream together first 4 ingredients.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix corn with onions, celery, green pepper, mustard, salt, lemon juice, fold in mayonnaise.
Chill thoroughly.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet.
Pinch together all dough.
Bake as instructions on roll or until golden brown. Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Spread mixture on cooled crescent roll cookie sheet. Sprinkle all veggies on top of cream cheese mixture (except tomatoes and black olives).
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of veggies.
Garnish with tomatoes and black olives.

title: orange glazed beets
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and add orange juice.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add rind and margarine.
Add beets to mixture.
Heat
thoroughly.
Makes
4 servings.

title: german chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Cook 2 more minutes. Remove from heat. Blend in melted chocolate. Blend in small amount of hot mixture into eggs. Return mixture to pan. Cook 1 minute. DO NOT BOIL. Remove from heat. Add coconut. Blend in cream. Chill 1 to 2 hours. Stir in nuts before freezing.

title: ranch dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended.
Serve with chips and vegetables.
Can also be used on baked potato as a topping.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and cinnamon in a pan (melt). Arrange nuts in tube pan.
Put dough on top of nuts.
Sprinkle dough with pudding.
Pour melted topping over dough.
(Cover.) Wrap with wax paper and then a towel.
Let rise overnight.

title: salisbury steak bake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup and rest of ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties and place into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; spoon off fat.
Mix rest of soup with 1/3 cup water and pour over patties.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Put in pie shells and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 1 hour or until apples are soft.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain grease.
Line baking dish with bread; pour sausage over bread.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt; pour over sausage.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine meat, egg, crackers and seasonings, mixing well with clean hands.
When thoroughly mixed, shape into balls using about 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mixture for each.
Place a cheese square in center of each (be sure meat mixture covers cheese).
Next put pizza balls into casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove from oven and drain all oil.
Add pizza sauce over top and return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: rotel casserole
directions: Chop pepper; mix with hamburger and brown.
Mix together. Pour into large casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: peach pie
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with oleo.
Slice peaches. Add 3 tablespoons sugar (less if desired) to peaches.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and buttermilk until well blended; pour evenly over entire layer of peaches.
Cut oleo into small pieces; place on top.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: southern apple pecan cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Empty cake mix and pudding mix in a bowl, add wesson oil and eggs. Beat together, add 7-Up. Pour into a large pan and bake as a sheet cake at 325° for 45 minutes. Leave in pan.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Saute white onions in oil; remove and drain.
In same oil, brown cut up chicken; remove and drain.
In same oil, add flour and cook on low heat until dark brown.
To brown roux, add water, chicken, onions and sausage; heat until low boil to melt all roux. Add green onions and parsley; continue to cook on medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Add file; cook additional 10 minutes.
Initial seasoning applied to raw meat.
Adjust seasoning midway
through cooking.
Skim excess oil after cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese straws
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix all ingredients together in mixer.
Press through cookie press to form a straw.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Or shape into 1-inch balls and roll into straws about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut to desired length.
Then bake as before.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Split cake into layers or cut into even slices.
Spread with jam and reassemble.
Cut into even 2-inch cubes.
Arrange cake cubes in individual serving bowls.
Sprinkle with sherry or cream sherry.
Wash and slice strawberries.
Reserve a few for garnish.
Add strawberries to cake in bowls.
Pour custard over cake and berries.
Drizzle with a little jam.
Cover.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Garnish trifle with sliced strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve within a few hours or trifle will become soggy.

title: rice bread
directions: Mash bananas in pan.
Pour in the pint of Cream of Rice and stir.
Add the ginger, baking powder and cooking oil.
Stir again until it becomes light.
Grease the baking pan; pour in the mixture.
Bake at 400° until it turns brown.
Allow it to stay in the oven for about 5 minutes before removing from oven.
Take it out of oven and serve.

title: chicken francese
directions: Lightly flour each piece of chicken.
Brown over medium heat. Place 2 slices of lemon on each piece of chicken and squeeze remainder of lemon juice over chicken.
Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with side dish of pasta.

title: corned beef hash with eggs
directions: Arrange hash slices in a buttered baking pan.
Press a hollow in the center of each and break an egg into it.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 325° or until the egg white is firm.

title: swedish noodles
directions: Let the hamburg, tomato sauce, salts and sugar simmer.
Stir cream cheese, sour cream and green onions together.
Layer 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of hamburg mixture and 1/2 of cream cheese mixture in removable crock.
Repeat layering with rest of mixtures.
Cover the entire top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes and then transfer the crock to the crock-pot on low setting until ready to serve.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Melt together in saucepan the butter, brown sugar and applesauce.
Drain all fruit.
Butter casserole.
Mix fruit together and add applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes. Add topping of 3 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Reheat.
This is delicious!

title: new orleans seafood gumbo
directions: Melt butter in large kettle over moderate heat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add okra and shrimp.
Cook stirring constantly, until shrimp start to turn pink. Add tomatoes, the liquid, water, bay leaves, parsley, thyme, cayenne and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add crab.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes longer.
Add oysters during last 10 minutes cooking time.
Add file powder, if desired, stirring constantly.
Don't allow gumbo to boil.
Serve on mounds of rice in soup bowls.
Recipe may be doubled and freezes nicely.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and margarine.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
