Sprinkle cracker crumbs and melted margarine over top of hash browns.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken bishop
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed.
Set aside.
In a casserole dish, layer chicken on the bottom without overlapping the pieces. Next, add the combo of both soups on top of chicken.
Layer the cheese making sure all sides are covered.
Spread cooked stuffing evenly over top of the entire dish.
Place uncovered in 350° preheated oven.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes or until stuffing is golden crispy.
Serves about 4 people.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put all ingredients together and mix well.
Make into small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350°
until browned.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Rub chicken and cavities with 2 tablespoons of olive oil, garlic and salt and pepper. Tuck wings under; tie legs together with string. Pour remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil into pan. Place chicken breast side up. Place lemon quarters into neck cavity and lower cavity. Bake at 450° and cook for 30 minutes; reduce temperature to 350° and cook for 2 1/2 hours.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Blend in milk, butter and egg, stir only enough to mix ingredients.
Fold in 1 cup thinly sliced apples, mixed with 1/4 cup sugar.
Fill 12 greased muffin pan cups 3/4 full.
Top with sugar mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: heloise's glazed carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook until just tender.
Combine cooking liquid with the juice from the can of pineapple tidbits. Thicken the carrot and pineapple juices with cornstarch.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add the carrots and pineapple; heat through.
A handful of coconut flakes may be tossed in.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Cook ground meat and drain well.
Cook sausage and drain well. Do not cook meat and sausage together.
Slowly melt cheese.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and Tabasco sauce to melted cheese and blend well. Stir in meat and sausage.
Ready to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Reheat in microwave, crock-pot or saucepan very slowly.
Be careful not to burn cheese.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Brown the steak, onion and celery and simmer.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Put all in a casserole and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ruth parker's mexican dip
directions: Layer in order listed in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate before serving with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and shrimp jambalaya
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add chicken, onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add rice; cook 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes and their liquid, chicken broth, parsley, basil and pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas.
Simmer, covered, 3 minutes until shrimp are cooked and chicken is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar and shortening; cream well.
Sift together flour and baking powder; alternate with milk in adding to sugar and shortening mixture.
Bake in 3 cake layer pans at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and pineapple; refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Cook pineapple juice with vinegar until thick and creamy.
Add egg, sugar and flour.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
After refrigeration of ingredients, combine with apples, peanuts and Cool Whip.

title: strawberry-angel food dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into small cubes; place in a large glass serving bowl and set aside.
Combine sour cream, milk and powdered sugar, stirring until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping; spoon evenly over cake.
Set aside.
Combine strawberry glaze and undrained strawberries; spoon evenly over dessert.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first five ingredients in 4-quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to boil over moderate heat, bring careful not to mistake air bubbles for boiling, then boil slowly, stirring constantly for 5 minutes (to soft ball stage).
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate and vanilla (nuts) until chocolate is melted.
Pour into two buttered pans (8 x 8-inches or 9 x 9-inches) and cool.
Cut before fudge hardens too much.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: nova scotia fish chowder
directions: Saute pork cut in small pieces.
Add onion, chopped fine. Cook slowly until tender, but do not brown.
Add potatoes and 2 cups water.
Add cut-up fish and simmer gently, stirring often. In another pot, heat milk, cracker crumbs, butter, parsley and seasoning.
Combine mixtures and stir over low heat until thoroughly blended and thickened.
Never allow to boil.
The secret lies in the slow cooking.
One half of the recipe could be made.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Coarsely chop graham crackers with food chopper.
Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream; beat with a whisk.
Pour half the filling over crust.
Slice bananas.
Layer on top.
Pour remaining filling over bananas.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate to set.

title: italian sausage and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice onion.
Pare potatoes; slice 1/4 inch thick.
Layer potato and onion rings in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Wash green pepper; cut into rings; arrange on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil. Pour salad oil and 1/2 cup water over the pepper.
Arrange sausage on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Remove foil; bake 1/2 hour longer, or until sausage is browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese puff
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut crusts off bread and butter each slice.

title: fruit of the sea(zuppa di pesce)
directions: Prepare Pizzaiola
Sauce
in very large skillet.
While sauce is cooking,
wash
and prepare all seafood.
Add lobster to sauce and cook for 8 minutes.
Add the rest of the seafood; cover skillet and
cook
on
medium heat an additional 15 minutes.
Boil linguine
accordingly
to
package directions and drain.
Divide linguine
evenly
among
plates.
Arrange a lobster in the center
of
linguine and 6 mussels and 6 clams around plate.
Pour sauce all over, dividing seafood among the 4 plates.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix until well blended.
Mash 3/4 cup of strawberry slices; add to cream cheese mixture.
Add powdered sugar to whipping cream; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold remaining strawberries into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Garnish with strawberries, cut in halves, around edge.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Spread on bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate. Combine cheeses. Sprinkle 1/2 over the cream cheese layer. Top with pizza sauce and pepper. Sprinkle with remaining cheeses. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with chips. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Mix together and shape into patties or croquettes.
Fry on both sides.
Adjust amounts to size can of salmon.
Add chili sauce or ketchup on top.

title: peanut butter & jelly sandwich pizzas
directions: Split and toast English muffin. Spread peanut butter on both sides of muffin. Spread jelly on the peanut butter. Top with bananas and drizzle with syrup. Sprinkle with coconut if desired.

title: mock champagne
directions: Combine pineapple juice, apple juice, lemonade concentrate and sugar.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Store in freezer overnight or longer.

title: biegnet
directions: Beat egg whites; add salt, baking powder, vanilla extract, sugar, margarine and milk.
Mix in flour until dough can be rolled without sticking to roller.
Roll dough until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut dough into 2-inch squares and cook in hot oil.
Turn the biegnets over as they rise in the oil and remove when amber in color. Cover the biegnets with powdered sugar and serve for breakfast with coffee or hot chocolate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Drop in paper bag with 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Shake well and place in Bundt pan or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter and one cup sugar in pan with raisins and nuts.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Take out of pan while hot.
Pull apart with fingers.

title: rhubarb-berry dessert
directions: Place cut up rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and flavored gelatin over the rhubarb.
Put miniature marshmallows on top.
Cover with cake mix that has been prepared per package directions.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium sized mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon on hot greased skillet and cook until golden brown, turning only once.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 3 eggs together.
Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Line sides and bottom of pan with crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° after filling with cream mixture.

title: chinese sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar, soy sauce, wine, vinegar and ketchup in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; add to sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sauce has thickened. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Put ingredients in order in large bowl.
Mix all together. Drop even teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Need 2 halves to each cookie.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Spray casserole with Pam. Slice potatoes and layer once on bottom of dish. Layer sliced onions once. Layer sliced zucchini once. Layer sliced tomatoes once. Layer with shredded Mozzarella cheese. Dot with butter. Repeat layering. Top with buttered bread crumbs or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are fork tender.

title: oat peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oats, corn syrup and vanilla. Mix well with spoon.
Pat into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Add oil to hot skillet and then stir-fry chicken quickly over high heat until pieces turn white (5 minutes).
Stir in wine, salt and cornstarch and lower heat.
Stir and watch until wine turns to gravy mixture (10 minutes).
Add green pepper (mushrooms optional) and cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over a bed of white rice.

title: chicken-green chili casserole
directions: Bone chicken and cut up into pieces.
Cut or tear the tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Mix soup, milk and onion.
Butter a 3 or 4-quart casserole and cover bottom with half of soup mixture.
Add a layer of tortilla strips and chunks of chicken. Top with layer of chilies.
Add remainder of soup mix and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
(Less time is required if using cooked chicken.)

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking pan.
Use reserved 3/4 cup stuffing mix to top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Place in buttered casserole dish, putting some mix, then a layer of eggs, then rest of the mix, making sure eggs are covered.
Sprinkle with crushed Rice Krispies. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-mushroom chowder(serves 8)
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
Wash and slice mushrooms.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine garlic, honey, soy sauce and ginger. In an 11 x 7-inch baking dish, arrange chicken breasts with thicker portions toward edges of dish.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of garlic mixture over chicken; cook, covered, on High for 6 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Rearrange and spoon juices over chicken halfway through cooking.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding sugar gradually, until right spread consistency.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Great served over chopped pork roast for sandwiches.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Heat oil in skillet and saute onions and garlic.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with minced parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Serve over hot buttered rice.

title: champignons aux fines herbs au gratin
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour over mushrooms and let stand for 2 hours, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon.
Drain off the oil marinade.
Heat 1/3 cup butter to smoking point over a fast flame; add mushroom slices and cook for 2 minutes.
Lower the flame and continue cooking for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon.
Transfer the contents to a generously buttered earthenware dish.
Spread over the top 1 cup buttered bread crumbs and brown the dish under the broiler.
Serve at once.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Cool and remove from bones.
Mix soups, tomatoes, onion and mushrooms together.
Add chicken.
Stir in Doritos.
Put in large baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Top with Doritos and cheese.
Place back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: praline yams
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place drained yams in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Sprinkle over yams.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 7 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and celery salt.
Pour over cereal.
Bake 1 hour in a 300° oven stirring every 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute beef and drain on paper towels.
Combine meal, eggs, milk, corn and bacon drippings.
Grease large iron skillet; heat. Sprinkle with a light layer of meal and brown slightly.
Put half of meal mixture in skillet.
Layer with cheese, meat, onions and pepper.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pat into 3 (8-inch) pie pans, then spread sour cream over the top.
Brown the ground beef and add spaghetti sauce.
Fill pies and top each pie with 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes, then slice.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes 15 minutes and cool and slice.
Then layer potatoes, both cheeses and butter in casserole dish until all are used.
Add milk and bake in oven 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly. Bake at 350°.

title: aunt cora's apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar, then add flour, salt and baking powder.
Next add vanilla, apples and nuts (hickory nuts or walnuts are best but any kind of nut can be used).
This is a thick dough.
Bake in a long pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix frozen orange juice and lemonade with water as instructed on cans.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Before serving, add ice and one-quart ginger ale.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Layer and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine everything except for oatmeal.
Boil mixture 1 1/2 minutes or until ball forms in cold water.
Then add oatmeal and spoon drop onto wax paper.

title: squashed squash
directions: Cook squash and mash.
Saute onion, cream and crackers in butter.
Put in casserole.
Put extra crackers and butter on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: quick and easy swiss steak in crock-pot
directions: Place serving size roast pieces into crock-pot.
Empty dry soup packages into small bowl.
Add 1 cup water.
Mix well.
Pour over roast pieces in crock-pot.
Cook at low setting for 10 to 12 hours or high setting for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over egg noodles with favorite vegetable and fruit.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set and golden.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together and pour the mixture evenly over the broccoli. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 4 hours, adding water.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, cook until broth starts to thicken and beans are very tender.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar and salt to taste, stirring well.
Serve with rice.

title: meal in a frypan
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave. Chop chipped beef into pieces and add to cream cheese. Add all remaining ingredients. Mix well. Chill 1 to 2 hours, form into a ball. Best if made a day early.
Serve and enjoy with your favorite crackers.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Place chickens in large kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt, curry, onion and celery.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove chicken; cool.
Strain broth.
Cool.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Slice mushrooms and saute in butter.
Reserve some slices for garnish.
Follow package directions for rice, using chicken broth for part of liquid. Combine ingredients in large casserole.
Arrange reserved mushrooms on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
To heat, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil, vanilla, flour and cinnamon. Add carrots and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Grease dish;
put in chicken, onion and eggs.
Mix soup and Veg-All;
pour
over
chicken.
Mix
flour, mayonnaise and milk and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt brown sugar and shortening in a saucepan, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients, then slowly add to other mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts and bake for 30 minutes.

title: busy woman's dream casserole
directions: Crumble raw ground beef in 9 x 9 inch baking dish. Cover with diced onion. Spread soup evenly over the mixture. place tater tots on top. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes, until bubbly and tater tots are brown.

title: dill pickles
directions: In each jar, put 2 heads of dill, a clove of garlic, alum and cucumbers.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to boil.
Pour over pickles and seal.
Turn upside-down for 3 to 4 hours.
Ready to eat in 6 weeks.

title: foolproof angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour and 1 cup sugar.
Sift together 4 times.
Set aside.
Sift remaining 1 cup sugar 4 times. Set aside.
(It is convenient to do this over waxed paper.)

title: sunday casserole
directions: Put everything in a casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve with noodles.

title: basic dip
directions: Mix well, serve with crackers, chips, or assorted veggies.

title: spareribs
directions: Marinate ribs in shoyu; brown ribs in oil.
Afterwards, drain off some oil; add ginger, salt, vinegar, sugar and pineapple syrup only.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Thicken with cornstarch; garnish with pineapple.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Bring the molasses to boiling point.
Remove from stove.
Add the shortening and soda.
Stir in the flour, baking powder, salt and ginger. Chill well.
Roll over very thin. Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: squash casserole 2
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on 325° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: chicken bones
directions: Cream together margarine and peanut butter.
Blend in sugar, crackers, coconut and vanilla.
Mix with fingers; shape into rolls about 3 inches long and about as big around as your fingers. Place on wax paper and chill.
Melt over hot water chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip rolls in chocolate and dry on wax paper.
Note: Put rolls in chocolate and lift out with forks-saves the marks that tongs would make.

title: patti's pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy. Then in another bowl, combine all dry ingredients. Add pumpkin mixture; mix thoroughly. Put into ungreased 15 x 9 x 1-inch pan. (Patti uses Pam.) Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool and frost.

title: home baked beans
directions: Rinse beans well, cover with water and cook until tender; do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Turn down heat to 250° and bake an additional 3 to 4 hours or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except broccoli, in a saucepan. Heat until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and mix.
Bake in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch buttered baking dish for 45 to 50 minutes or until broccoli is done.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Take sour cream out and allow to come to room temperature. Finely chop bell peppers.
Drain and chop pimentos.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread mixture on individual tortillas and roll tightly.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; secure by laying open side down.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice in 1/2-inch thickness.
Good party food.

title: impossible egg custard
directions: Beat eggs until they are lemon in color.
Add to the eggs 1/2 of the sugar, flour and milk; beat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat again.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese corn bake
directions: Melt
butter
with cheese.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix together dressing, preserves, water and soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour covered at 350°.
Remove from oven and add bell pepper and pineapple.
Bake 30 minutes more uncovered.

title: squizzle
directions: Brown hamburger; drain, put in casserole dish.
Put both cans of vegetable soup on top of hamburger.
Top with mashed potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika and pats of butter.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes until brown and stiff.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise.
Place 1 layer in casserole dish. Top with desired amount of onion.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Add another layer of hot dogs, onion and brown sugar.
Repeat until all hot dogs are used.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until soup is bubbly (about 30 minutes). Serves approximately 4.
Bake uncovered.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake until golden brown.
Top with icing.

title: honey lime dressing(for fresh fruit)
directions: In saucepan, cook egg, juice and honey until thick.
Blend in salt and mace; cool.
Add sour cream.

title: grandma's king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add soups, tomatoes, garlic and chili powder (to taste).
Place tortillas in chicken broth for 10 minutes.

title: herbed peas
directions: Saute the green onions in the butter in a saucepan for 5 minutes, or until they are tender, but not browned.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 25 minutes, or until peas are tender.
Serves 4.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Put apples in buttered baking dish.
Mix all the other ingredients and spread on top.
It will spread out.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kelley jo and gan's easy cookies
directions: Choose a cake mix and add eggs and vegetable oil (if you want, you can add raisins, nuts, coconut, etc.).
Mix well and use a teaspoon to drop on ungreased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool, eat and share.

title: apricot delight(dessert)
directions: Crumble angel food cake into a large cake pan. Trim off outside of cake. Cook together apricot nectar, cornstarch and sugar until it becomes thick and clear.
Pour over angel food cake and chill until firm. Top with Cool Whip.

title: consomme stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushrooms and nuts. Beat in eggs (mixing them in separate bowl first.) Mix.
Add sauteed mixture and consomme.
Mix well.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add applesauce mixed with soda, baking powder, cinnamon and flour.
Then add raisins.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: a crackling good apple pie
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients to eggs. Beat well.
Add nuts and apples; mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased 9-inch square dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiceland methodist's mincemeat oatmeal drops(in honor of sherry's honor)
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg, mincemeat and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in the oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: milligatawny soup
directions: Remove any excess fat from chicken.

Heat chicken, giblets (except liver), neck, water, salt, curry powder, lemon juice, cloves and mace to boiling in Dutch oven. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until thickest pieces of chicken are done, about 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots.
Add a pinch of salt to water.
Drain.
Mash carrots when cooked.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° until done.
Very good dish to take to potluck dinners.
Always a hit! Serves 8.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Place between graham crackers and freeze overnight on cookie sheet.
Wrap in foil and keep in freezer.
Makes 12 to 15 sandwich squares.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover with enough water to cook shrimp and corn.
Cook until the shrimp are firm.
Serve hot.

title: truck stop fries, gravy and cheese
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise into thin wedges (leave peeling on). Spray a 12-inch pizza pan with nonstick spray coating.
Place potato wedges in a single layer on the pan.
Spray the tops of potatoes with coating.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mrs. coley's waffles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl until moist.
(Will be thick.)
Mix soda with water and add to mixture.
Stir well.
(Will be thin.)
Let set 10 minutes.
(Will become light and fluffy.) Makes excellent pancakes and waffles.

title: senator russell's sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add melted margarine. Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all
of
the ingredients except orange juice.
Bake cake at 350°
until
baked.
While
cake is hot, poke holes in cake with a fork and pour hot orange juice over the cake.
Let cool.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy and add egg yolk and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour until smooth and blended. (Dough will be thick.)
Spread evenly on ungreased 16 x 14 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and arrange unwrapped candy bars evenly near surface of crust. Let stand for 5 minutes to soften.
Spread over crust and sprinkle nuts over top.
Cut into squares.

title: crescent roll taco pockets
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion. Open crescent rolls. Lay out each dough section. Open chile and lay on crescent roll section. Fill with ground beef and some cheese. Put another crescent roll on top and pinch together. Bake as directed on crescent roll can. Garnish with tomatoes, sour cream, salsa and onion.

title: cherry cheese torte
directions: Using 8 or 9 inch round layer cake pans, make and cool cake as directed on package.
Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar, nutmeg and milk; beat until smooth.
Split each layer into 2 thin layers. Spread 1/2 cup cream cheese mixture and 1/2 c. cherry pie filling between each layer and on top of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mac and cheese casserole delight
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed; stir in tuna, onion, peas and celery salt to taste.

title: graham pudding
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Add to crumbs and form a crust in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Real good.

title: cheese danish
directions: Mix egg, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla all together.

title: velvet mashed potato chocolate cake(date 1868)
directions: Peel the 2 medium potatoes; cover with water and boil unti tender, about 25 minutes.
Mash thoroughly; do not add milk or seasonings.
Measure out 1 cup; cover to keep warm and set aside. Preheat the oven to 300°.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 13 x 9-inch pan per directions.
While cake bakes, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
When cake is done, poke holes in it and pour Jell-O over it.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil spaghetti while cooking other ingredients.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain grease.
Add soups plus 1 soup can of water.
Cook until mixture bubbles.
In a large casserole dish, make layers of spaghetti, sauce, grated cheese and chopped olives. Bake about 20 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix together the flour, brown sugar and stick of butter (softened).
Reserve 1 cup for later use. Add the milk, baking soda, salt, egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle reserved mixture on top of batter.
Crush the Heath bars while still in the package with a hammer or meat cleaver.
Open the packages and sprinkle on top of batter. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pina colada popcorn
directions: In microwave-safe
bowl,
melt	margarine on High until melted.
Add
sugar,
corn	syrup, pineapple juice concentrate and rum extract.
Microwave
on
High
until it boils, about 3 minutes, stirring once.
Microwave	on High for 3 or 4 minutes without stirring.

title: lemon delight
directions: Work together flour and
margarine
like
a
pie crust. Add chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; beat in sugar, honey, butter and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir until just evenly moistened.
Stir in granola and nuts.
Add zucchini.
Spoon into muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion until brown.
Add meat and seasonings.
Brown and drain grease.
Add drained green beans and soup.
Pour into casserole.
Spoon mounds of mashed potatoes over top of meat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to the package.
Drain and place in a buttered casserole dish.

title: governor martz's favorite chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: meat ball tidbits and sauce
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together (add milk if necessary). Shape into balls.
Brown or steam; drain off grease.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add Kool-Aid, sugar, lemon juice, pineapple juice and water. Freeze. Remove from freezer 2 or 3 hours before serving and flake with a fork until slushy.

title: egg custard (pie)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Cream in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Melt oleo and add to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a
oven
for	30
to 35 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Line 24 muffin tins with paper liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Blend cream cheese, lemon juice, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Spoon enough mixture in tins to half fill.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool; top with the pie filling.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add water and mix like bread dough.
Add food coloring for desired colors.
Keep in plastic bag.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch and then add water. Bring to a boil and thicken. Take off stove and add jello and cool. Put strawberries in pie crusts and pour cool mixture over them. Put in refrigerator 2 1/2 hours. After they jell, top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: apple-walnut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; put aside. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well.
Blend in flour mixture. Fold in apples and nuts.
Grease 2 large loaf pans and flour.
Tap out excess flour.
Recipe makes 2 loaves.
Some nuts may be placed on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stopwatch pasta salad
directions: Mix and set aside to add to pasta.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into greased pan and bake at 400 degrees for approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Pour almost all of the oil off.
Add onion.
When soft, add tomatoes, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
If not thickened, add a little cornstarch. Add wine the last 15 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar gradually.
Then stir in Cool Whip gradually.
Pour into pie shell.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 8.

title: easy delicious chocolate mousse
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Stir in brandy.
Separate eggs, putting whites into deep bowl and stirring yolks into chocolate.
Beat egg whites until frothy, add sugar as you beat them until stiff.
Gently fold chocolate mixture into beaten egg whites until thoroughly blended.
Put mixture in four dessert cups and place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts to serve.

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine fruit, coconut and nuts.
Let stand.
Combine cake mix, oil and pudding.
Beat well.
Batter will be sticky and thick.
Fold in brandied fruit, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: date fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts with flour.
Beat eggs; add sugar gradually, then fruit and nuts.
Bake at 200° to 250° for 3 hours. Line pan with greased brown paper bag.

title: raisin honey cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add honey, then eggs, flour, etc. Add oats and raisins last.
Bake on top shelf of oven at 350° until lightly browned.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt together the butter and brown sugar; let cool.
Add egg, flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° until firm (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Will look like brownies.
May double recipe for larger batch.
Yields 12 to 16 squares.

title: savory southwest salsa
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water for 30 to 60 seconds until skins loosen.
Dip in cold water; slip off skins.
Core and chop tomatoes.
In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes or to desired thickness.
Immediately fill hot pint jars with salsa, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Carefully run a non-metallic utensil down inside of jars to remove trapped air bubbles.
Wip jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars; screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 15 minutes.

title: pepperoni rolls(bread machine rolls)
directions: Follow your recipe for butter rolls or pan rolls in your bread machine cookbook.
When finished, divide dough into 12 rolls.
One at a time, flatten and spread dough.
Place 10 or 12 slices of pepperoni on one side of the dough.
Place 1 tablespoon mozzarella cheese on the pepperoni.
Fold the other side of the dough over the pepperoni and cheese and seal the edges.
Repeat the process for the remaining rolls.
Bake according to your bread machine recipe. Enjoy!

title: taco dip #2
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce on top.
Add chopped onion, lettuce and tomato.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill.
Serve with taco chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil. Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Stir until heated through.
Pour into a casserole, greased with margarine, and sprinkle with crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mushroom delight
directions: Drop fresh mushrooms into boiling water for 1 minute; drain and immerse in ice water until completely chilled.
Remove and drain thoroughly.
Meanwhile, combine next 6 ingredients in small bowl and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and continue to mix well.
Alternately spoon the mushrooms and vinegar mixture into quart container.
Cover and chill.

title: janet's blue ribbon zucchini cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
May be poured into a sheet cake pan.
Oil and flour the cake pans.
Bake in a 325° oven until brown on top, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and Parkay until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar. Beat well.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well.
Alternate addition of flour and milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and butter flavoring.
Fold in egg whites (beaten stiff, but not dry).
(Note:
Beat cake well.)
Spray tube pan with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on wire rack.

title: old fashioned icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and nuts. Shape dough into 2 rectangles (5 x 3 x 1 1/2-inch). Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Place about 2-inches apart.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool, then glaze.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl toss all ingredients.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Baking time is 5 hours.

title: triple treat popcorn
directions: Combine popcorn, shoestring potatoes and peanuts.
Melt butter.
Add garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and dill weed. Pour over popcorn.
Mix and toss well.
Bake at 225° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin pans or use paper cups. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt, soda and poppy seed. Spoon into muffin tins and bake about 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9-inch aluminum foil baking pan.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup and milk in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Combine water and butter in bowl.
Stir into partially melted butter.
Add stuffing mix.
Stir gently until water is absorbed.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pierogi
directions: Sift flour and salt in a bowl.
Add eggs and egg whites. Knead to make smooth, glossy dough, adding a little water if needed.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Roll out dough thinly and cut into 2 1/2 to 3-inch rounds.
Place a piece of fruit in center and fold over.
Press edges to seal.
Cook the dumplings in simmering salt water for 10 to 15 minutes, until they float.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Drain on a paper towel and pile up in a warm serving bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar, then pour the melted butter and cream.
May be heated by frying in melted butter.

title: stuffed baked clams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and garlic in the olive oil.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Mix together clams, sauteed onions and garlic, bread crumbs, grated cheese, salt, pepper, oregano and parsley.
Add enough of the reserved clam liquid to make mixture moist.
Place mixture in individual clam shells (these can be purchased at kitchenware shops).
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with additional grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked butter beans
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; pour into a greased baking dish and place slices of bacon on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Add dry ingredients stirring until moistened. Spoon batter into well greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: orange fudge
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan with 1/2 tsp. butter. In a heavy saucepan combine the sugar, cream and remaining butter. Cook over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 4 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in chips and marshmallow creme until smooth.

title: cream of tartar biscuits
directions: Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening and add milk, using a fork to mix.

title: cheesy meat pie
directions: Brown ground beef in butter; add onion.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Spread over pie crust; add cheese, potato and carrot. In bowl, mix milk, eggs and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat and cheese.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Servings: 2.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook onions and broccoli and drain.
Melt butter and stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thick. Add broccoli, onions, cheese and broth.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: dinner casserole
directions: Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake until brown.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in saltwater until tender.
Drain water or cook squash until almost all water has cooked out.
Add sugar, butter, salad dressing, 1/2 of cheese and crackers.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining crackers and cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: appetizer
directions: Marinate chestnuts in Worcestershire sauce (a few minutes or a few hours). Roll chestnuts in sugar, then wrap up in bacon. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bacon is cooked.

title: lilikoi jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin
in
water.
Pour hot water over jello and sugar.
Add
gelatin,
lilikoi
juice and lemon juice into jello mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan and chill.

title: broccoli, chili and artichoke pasta
directions: Cook the pasta in a large saucepan of boiling salted water according to the instructions on the packet until it is al dente. Add the broccoli for the last 3 minutes cooking time. Drain, reserving a little of the cooking water.

title: beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Bring to boil and drain off water. Add onion, garlic powder, beer, cilantro, bacon, salt (optional) and more water.
Cook until done.

title: cabbage cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, stir milk into soup.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir in cabbage and carrot.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is done.
Stir in cheese, caraway and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, salt, garlic powder and chives.
Fold in crabmeat.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli for about 7 minutes in microwave; drain. Add 1/2 stick margarine with Velveeta cheese.
Top with Ritz crackers combined with 1/2 stick margarine which has been melted. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Add vegetables, as much as you want.
Mix with enough mayonnaise to make mixture creamy.
Sprinkle with a little dry Ranch dressing and mix.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; spread bread slices with butter. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and set aside.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.

title: groovy cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger meat, drain off grease.
Put into crock-pot, add rest of ingredients and stir until cheese is melted.
Cook additional 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
Add salt to taste. Drain broccoli.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Combine broccoli mixture with 1/8 stick margarine. Put mixture in buttered casserole dish.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion until meat is no longer pink.
Add the soup mix.
Place meat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer vegetables over meat.
Heat the soup and milk and pour over meat and vegetables.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften butter and add flour.
Knead.
Add cheese and mix until it forms a ball. Take small amount of dough and wrap around an olive. Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat to boiling, water and oleo.
Remove from heat and add 1 c. flour; stir until blended.
LET COOL 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 400°F, 30-35 minutes. LET COOL.

title: cheese balls
directions: Bring to a boil in 2-quart saucepan the water, salt, nutmeg and butter.
Add flour all at once.
Remove from heat and stir until mixture forms ball and leaves side of pan.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Add cheese and stir until blended.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Trim outside skin off round steak and cut into serving-size pieces (6 or 7).
Spread each piece with mustard.
Lay a piece of bacon on each piece.
Roll up, secure with toothpicks or string. Roll in flour.
Fry in grease until brown.
Remove meat, pour off all grease but leave browned particles in pan.
Put meat back in, add water just to cover.
Stir and simmer slowly, covered, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if necessary, to keep from sticking to pan.

title: lollipops
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, vinegar and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat; add butter and salt.
Cool until slightly thick.
Place 16 wooden skewers 5 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Drop candy from tablespoons over skewers to form 3-inch lollipops.

title: rich's spaghetti sauce
directions: First boil chicken and then dice up chicken.
Put in crock-pot. Then add crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, garlic cloves, allspice, parsley and oregano.
Cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in crock-pot.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Saute onion, broccoli and butter for about 10 minutes.
Add to rest of mix and bake in greased pan for about 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Combine chicken, salt and soy sauce and let stand for 15 minutes.
In a large skillet, add cooking oil and rice.
Brown until lightly browned.
Add chicken and broth; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Uncover and add vegetables; simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer and then add scrambled eggs.

title: shrimp casserole superb
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: moravian sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, soda mixture and lemon flavoring. Slowly add flour until you have a soft dough ball. Roll and cut with cookie cutters. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 265° until light brown.

title: neapolitan lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and set aside, covered.
Crumble beef into 2-quart glass mixing bowl.
Cook on High (maximum power) for 4 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Pour off drippings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Saute garlic, green pepper, red pepper, mushrooms, yellow onion and any other favorite vegetable in a separate pan, saute your Italian sausage.
Boil your tortellini according to directions.
Drain oil from vegies and sausage.
Stir together Roma tomatoes, Parmesan cheese, black pepper, olive oil, a few tablespoons for vegies and 1/2 cup chicken broth.

title: a complete meal casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan lightly.
Press ground beef into casserole dish.
Layer on onions.
Spread on mixed vegetables. Spread on potatoes.
Layer on soup and sprinkle 1 teaspoon of onion soup mix on top of each layer.
Cover pan with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: preserving children
directions: Mix children and puppies together well; put in acre, stirring constantly.
Pour brooks and pebbles.
Sprinkle acre with flowers. Spread over with blue sky and bake all in hot sun.
When brown, remove and set in bathtub to cool.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Place chicken or turkey in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Place on top of chicken or turkey.
Sprinkle the stuffing on top.
Melt butter in broth. Bring to boil and pour on top of stuffing.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add milk and extract.
Starting with a cold oven, bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° in tube pan.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: real corn bread
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Beat egg in bowl.
Add milk and oil.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients all at once, stirring just enough to get all the lumps out.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together with mixer until well blended. Better if marinated a few hours or overnight.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and put into casserole dish.
Top with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, oil and sour cream.
Add cake mix, pudding and chocolate chips; mix well.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cut large marshmallows in 8 pieces.
Mix sugar, milk, butter and marshmallows and cook on very low heat until marshmallows melt, about 5 minutes.
Remove from burner; add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Have a pan, 8-inch square, buttered and sprinkled with nuts.
Beat fudge until well mixed and pour immediately over nuts in pan as fudge hardens quickly.

title: bisquick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add Bisquick and mix well. Knead well until smooth on floured board.
Form into rolls.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: hungarian cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Slice onion very thin.
Put both in a bowl and salt heavily.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Squeeze (with hand) cucumbers and onion to get all the water out.
Mix with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl; add oil, sour cream and salt.
Mix well.
Sift in baking powder with the corn meal and stir into egg mixture.
Mix in peppers, chili powder and creamed corn.
Beat with wooden spoon for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of mix into greased 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Top with remaining batter, then rest of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Recipe can also be cut in half and baked in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and Karo syrup.
Return to heat; stir until sugar dissolves.
Turn heat down and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Cook to soft ball stage; remove from heat and stir in butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Turn into greased pan to harden.
The secret of good fudge is the beating!!

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour. Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: scrappy crackers
directions: Place dry Ranch dressing mix and dill over crackers.
Toss. Pour oil over mixture slowly and mix well.
Oil will disappear.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill well before serving.

title: godfather meat loaf
directions: Mix on wax paper; shape into rectangle.
Layer 4 slices ham and 4 slices Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Pour 1 jar Ragu Italian sauce over meat loaf; top with 2 slices Mozzarella cheese.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box; let set until jelly like. Mix pudding mix with water and lemon juice in saucepan; boil until thick.
Cool.
Add jello, pudding and whipped topping, beating with mixer until well mixed.
Fold in berries.
Pour in graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate banana pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Additional water may be added to control thickness of pancake.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Chop drained pimentos. Mix with cheese, mustard and mayonnaise. Allow to sit at room temperature for 30 minutes so flavors will blend. This keeps a week in the refrigerator. Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water and oleo until melted.
Take off stove and add flour; let cool.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: broccoli mushroom casserole
directions: Arrange vegetables in layers in a heavily greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients together.
Spread over vegetables. Top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix first 6 dry ingredients together in large bowl.
In a small saucepan, combine oil, honey and vanilla.
Heat over low heat until mixture is warm enough to blend together.
Pour wet mixture into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
The secret to a crunchy granola is to make sure that every particle is completely coated with liquid.
Spread mixture into 2 or 3 large baking pans and toast in low 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Stir every 10 or 15 minutes.
Granola is done when golden brown.
Remove from oven and stir in raisins.
Cool completely in pan, then store in airtight container and refrigerate.
Makes 5 1/2 pounds granola.

title: fudge nut brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine chocolate pieces, cream cheese and evaporated milk. Stir over low heat until smooth. Stir in nuts. Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream the sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Press half of flour mixture onto bottom of a 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread chocolate mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crust mixture.

title: irish brown soda bread
directions: Note:
To sour 2 1/2
cups milk, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar and let
stand
10 to 15 minutes until thickened and curdled.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt 1/3 cup of butter in large saucepan.
Add onions and saute until golden; then remove and set aside.
Melt 1/3 cup more of the butter.
Add mushrooms and saute until lightly browned, then remove and set aside.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan. Roll beef in flour and saute in butter until browned.
Add bouillon, salt and onions.
Cover and simmer gently until beef is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Then add Worcestershire sauce; sour cream and mushrooms, heat thoroughly.
For fluffy rice, prepare 4 or 5 cups packaged precooked rice as directed on package.
Spoon beef stroganoff over rice.

title: mary ellen's chocolate sauce
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Stir in sugar and cocoa until very well blended.
Add milk gradually and stir until thick.
Serve warm over ice cream.
This sauce keeps very well in the refrigerator.
When cold, it is very thick. When using again, reheat it in the microwave.

title: seafood fettuccine
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half, stir until thickened and add Parmesan.
Cook and stir until smooth. Fold in crab, heat 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss fettuccine with sauce and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes or microwave until soft. Mash with peels on, stirring in milk. Blend in blender adding more milk to desired consistency. Pour into soup tureen, adding garden vegetables and stirring in lightly. Salt, pepper and butter to taste.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan and bake.
Mix cream cheese with enough sugar to taste and spread over cooled cookie.
Then cover with fresh fruit, top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and spices.
Add eggs, soda, flour and salt.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Prepare jello as it says on package.
Instead of cold water, use orange juice.
Chill until it starts to thicken, then beat in cream cheese.
Chill, cut and serve.
You may also add pineapple or mandarin oranges.

title: pierogies
directions: Potatoes have to be boiled.
Bacon cut up in bits and onion cut up.
Then fry together.
Mash potatoes, add fried bacon and onion, salt and pepper and mix together.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with your favorite strawberry icing.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
When it starts to boil, turn off and add cake mix.
Beat.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Put chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° until done, about 25 minutes.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Wash berries thoroughly; remove caps and crush berries.
Heat slowly to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and continue cooking rapidly until mixture gives test for jelly.
Test by drawing the spoon across the center of the pan.
If the mark does not fill in quickly, the jam
is thick enough.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.
If seedless jam is desired, rub cooked berries through sieve before adding sugar.
Makes 2 pints.

title: celery salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil and reserve half of vinegar.
Put in blender; beat on high speed.
Pour in oil slowly and add remaining vinegar slowly.
Then chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then shape into ball and roll in crushed pecans.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix all together.
Put in large casserole dish or 2 small casseroles.
Top with grated cheese (may use crushed potato chips).
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the pie filling. Pour half of mixture in a round cake pan.
Spread filling on top of mixture, then cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: p.b.  sesame cookies
directions: Bake sesame seed until golden brown.
Cream sugars and margarine.
Beat in peanut butter and egg.
Combine flour, 2 tablespoons seed, salt, soda and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten crisscross fashion with fork.
Sprinkle with remaining seed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish greased with butter the Veg-All, soup and onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt 1/2 stick butter; crush crackers.
Mix together.
Add more butter if needed.
Crumble over casserole and cook 10 more minutes.
Serve warm.

title: grandma's cheese sauce
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the flour; blend thoroughly.
When perfectly smooth, add seasonings, then milk.
Stir constantly over low burner until sauce boils.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add grated cheese, stirring constantly while adding.
Suitable for fish and vegetables.

title: kentucky cabbage casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in salted water until tender.
Drain, then combine the next 3 ingredients and add to the cabbage mixture.
Stir well.
Put in a Pyrex dish.
Can be topped with Premium fat free crackers.
Cook in 350° oven until bubbly. Contains approximately 410 calories.

title: grandma's muffins
directions: In a large bowl, sift first 4 ingredients, then stir in next 6.
Beat together the last 3 items, then pour into dry ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: credulous cranberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 1-pound loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients. Bake in loaf pan in a preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions.
Add dry cake mix to the cooked pudding; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of cake. Bake at 375° until done.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together peanut butter and margarine over low heat.
Pour the mixture over the sugar and mix well.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir well.
Stir in walnuts. Shape mixture into 2 cheese balls and sprinkle with paprika. Chill 8 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Yield:
4 3/4 cups.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add vanilla wafers that have been crushed.
Add pecans and roll into balls. Roll into coconut and put in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix above well and bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake meat loaf 1/2 hour, then put sauce on top and bake 1/2 hour.

title: eggs over mashed potatoes
directions: Distribute mashed potatoes into 4 au gratin dishes; smooth. Place 1 egg in center of each dish.
Spoon cheese sauce over each egg.
Goes well with a brunch of juice, fresh fruit and hot drink.

title: avocado pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss pasta with dressing.
Add remaining ingredients, except avocado; toss gently.
Season to taste.
Fan avocado slices on top.
Garnish with fresh basil leaves and tomato.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Place caramels and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan.
Heat over medium to low heat, stirring continually, until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into pie crust. Combine cream cheese, sour cream, and milk in a blender.
Process until smooth.
Add pudding mix; process for about 30 seconds longer.

title: low-fat, low sodium sweet and spicy popcorn
directions: Spray a cold 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Place popcorn in the baking pan.

title: mexican haystacks
directions: Crush a handful of chips and place on a plate.
Add a layer of chili, then rice.
Stack layers of lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onion.
Add taco sauce to taste.
Delicious!

title: bourbon balls
directions: Pour sugar into medium bowl. Add melted butter. Season to taste with bourbon. Chill in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Roll mixture into 1-inch balls. Dip into chocolate and paraffin wax mixture.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese; sprinkle over pineapple.
Spread crackers over top and pour margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: chili
directions: Mix all together and place in crock-pot; cook 6 to 8 hours.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut
shortening
into flour.
Beat together the other 3 ingredients and
add to flour mixture.
Toss lightly to form a ball.
Makes 2 crusts.
Freezes well.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together walnuts, dates, raisins, brown and white sugars, then put baking soda into 1 cup of boiling water and dissolve.
Pour on top of mixture, then add 1/2 cup plain boiling water and mix together.
Let cool, then beat egg and add to cooled mixture and mix well.
Next, mix butter, orange rind and vanilla; pour into mixture.
Pour flour into mixture, one cup at a time.
Brush pan with melted butter and fill 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter (softened to room temperature). Stir in flour.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: pennsylvania dutch chicken pot pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening, cut enough milk in to moisten so it will hold together.
Roll out as thin as possible and cut to make noodles.
In large kettle, alternate noodles, potatoes and chicken until used up. Pour hot broth from chicken over all layers and boil until done, about 15 minutes.
May season with onion, salt, celery seed or parsley flakes.

title: nutmeg cake
directions: Blend sugar, flour and shortening to a crumbly mixture.
Put half of these crumbs into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Stir nutmeg into remaining crumbs, then add egg.
Stir soda into sour cream and blend into crumb mixture.
Pour over crumb layer in pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well until blended.
Add raisins and nuts; drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut out center of bread.
Pour dip in bread as if it were a bowl.

title: green bean creole
directions: Saute bacon in skillet.
Add onion, flour, salt and tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add beans to mixture and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter and egg yolks.
Boil on medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla. Pour in prebaked pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff, add 2 teaspoons sugar per egg, and top pie.
Bake until brown.

title: red enchilada sauce
directions: Heat oil and brown flour.
To 2 cups of water (or stock), add chili powder and dissolve.
Add chili to browned flour and mix well.
Add seasonings and blend.
Bring to a bubbly boil, stirring frequently.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 1 1/4 cups of sauce.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese
until smooth. Stir in other ingredients. Chill.
Serve with vegetables or chips.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: lamb pilaf
directions: In two batches, quickly brown half the lamb in 2 tablespoons of butter over high heat.
Remove and set aside.
Lower heat to medium and saute onions, cinnamon, pepper and garlic powder for 3 to 5 minutes until onions are opaque.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage.
Drain and cool.
Mix other ingredients in large bowl.
Add sausage and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle some of the cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together lightly to prevent mashing the cooked rice. Place in buttered casserole dish and bake in moderate 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: crab casserole
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix in the milk until creamy.
Add the remaining ingredients, except almonds.
Refrigerate for one day.
Put mixture into small casserole.
Sprinkle with the slivered almonds.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve while warm with unsalted crackers.

title: eggs and sausage
directions: Distribute bread cubes on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut sausage into bite-sized pieces.
Spread over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top next.
Blend eggs and milk and pour over all. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scotch cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Place margarine, cocoa, shortening and water in a saucepan and bring to a rapid boil, stirring.
Pour mixture into flour/sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana cake with butter cream frosting
directions: Cut up the bananas and place in a small bowl.
Beat with a mixer.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together sugar and 1/2 c. margarine. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add buttermilk.
Beat constantly, add mashed banana and flour mixture alternately.
Pour into
9 inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: hawaiian wieners
directions: Cut the wieners into bite sized pieces.
Take a toothpick and put a piece of wiener and pineapple on it.
Make up as many as you like and put them on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together until smooth for frosting.
Beat well.

title: omelet-dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and powdered sugar in a small mixing bowl.
Beat well with a fork.
Heat butter in a 7 to 8-inch oven-proof omelet pan. When foaming, add omelet mixture. Allow bottom to set slightly.
Finish under a hot broiler until top is set and lightly browned.
Fill with Mandarin Orange Filling.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Add a little hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Cook about 3 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour over bananas in pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: holly leaves
directions: Put butter and marshmallows in a large bowl and place in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and add green food coloring. Stir until color is even.
Add corn flakes and stir until coated. Put all the mixture onto wax paper.
Make small leaves and add 2-3 red hots for berries.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain fat.
Add tomato paste, sauce and 2 (8 ounce) cans water.
Stir; add macaroni, carrots and onion soup mix; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add corn and cook until desired consistency.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove most of the bacon from pan and add onions.
Saute until soft.
Put corn through a food processor or blender and add to onions and bacon.
Cook until
mixture begins to brown.
Add butter; when melted, stir in flour.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Stir in the cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve in bowls.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: soft chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift and add cocoa, flour, soda and salt and add alternately with sour cream.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Step 1:
Cut up green onions in a large bowl.
Mix cabbage and green onions.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place crackers in single layer in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, combine Worcestershire, 1 tablespoon cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder; blend well.
Pour over crackers and toss to coat.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Cool and store in covered container.

title: amish cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Form small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco sauce
directions: Cook 1/2 cup onion and garlic in oil for five minutes.
Add tomato juice and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain and add salt to taste and as much cayenne as you can take.

title: karo pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in uncooked pie shell for 10 minutes at 450°, then for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cider drink
directions: Simmer 1 1/2 cups apple cider to remaining ingredients, then pour to remaining apple cider.
Serve with cinnamon stick, if desired.

title: elsie's congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pineapple juice and crushed pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip mixture according to directions on the package.
Combine Jell-O and Dream Whip and whip 2 minutes. Add Mandarin oranges and chill overnight.

title: seasoned squid rings
directions: Clean and cut squid; put aside.
Mix Italian seasoning, garlic powder, onion powder, and bread crumbs together and set aside. Beat egg and mix in milk.
Heat shortening in a deep fry pan.
Dip rings in egg and cover with crumbs.
Fry until golden brown. Garnish and serve.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in order given and pour in large pan.
Bake.
Cool 20 minutes before cutting.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel nut frosting
directions: Boil sugar and water until it forms threads.
Pour gradually while beating in beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until nearly cool.
Place pan over hot water and cook white stirring constantly until mixture becomes granular around the edge of the pan.
Remove from pan of water and beat well until it will hold shape.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour on cake; spread leaving a rough surface.

title: colorado pine nut salad(serves 6)
directions: Toast pine nuts under broiler until golden brown; watch carefully.
Set aside.

title: sweet dills
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pickling spices.
Put on stove.
Keep lid on and let simmer.
Stir occasionally.
Put garlic (1), dill, pepper (1 slice) and onion at bottom of each jar.
Cut pickles in half lengthwise.
Fill half full with pickles.
Repeat with garlic, dill, etc.
Fill with pickles and repeat garlic, dill, etc.
On top layer, add 1 bay leaf and sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed.
Bring vinegar mix to boil. Pour through strainer and fill each jar to the top.
Let cool for a day, rotating (flipping) jars for mixing every few hours. Refrigerate.
Makes approximately 40 pickles or 4 to 8 quarts.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water until tender.
Drain. Mix soup, sour cream, and cheese whiz.
Add chicken, broccoli, rice, chestnuts, celery, onion, salt, and pepper.
Add pimento last.
Put in a 9x13-inch dish.
Mix cracker crumbs and oleo. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350 for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and butter, in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Continue to boil until ingredients reach soft ball stage (approximately 224° to 226° in Roswell). Remove saucepan from heat.
Let ingredients stand until they reach 100°.
Beat until fudge turns dull.
Quickly add butter and vanilla.
Then pour fudge into greased pan.

title: chile verde
directions: Brown meat, onion and spices together in a large skillet or saucepan. Leave meat drippings in pan, then sprinkle 1/2 cup flour over top of meat and mix together. Add enough water to make gravy. Add chiles and tomatoes, if used.
Let simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
If gravy is too thick, add water.
If too thin, make a flour or cornstarch paste and add to gravy.

title: milnot pie
directions: Mix jello with hot water and let chill until slightly thickened.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip Milnot milk that has been chilled, then blend all other ingredients including jello together and add to milk mixture.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust, then chill.

title: cindy's apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and apples.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased bread pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: springtime punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon, orange and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate. Just before serving, combine with ginger ale in a large punch bowl.
Yields 16 to 20 servings (3 quarts).

title: caramel pie
directions: Remove label from sweetened condensed milk.
Place unopened can in cooking pan and cover with water.
Boil for 3 hours, then cool.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and soak in salted water for at least 1 hour.
Drain and place in a large bowl or pan.
Sprinkle McCormick chicken seasoning over chicken pieces and mix well with hands. Combine flour, salt, pepper and Creole seasoning in large plastic bag.
Add a few pieces of chicken at a time.
Shake to coat.
Heat Crisco oil in large heavy skillet until very hot.
Fry chicken until golden brown on one side.
Turn once for even browning. Drain on paper towel.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter or margarine.
Mix with sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in cocoa.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Blend eggs, honey, oil and vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture, alternating with zucchini.
Fold in nuts.
Divide mixture between 2 buttered and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool inverted on cake rack.

title: taco salads
directions: For meat mixture, in a large skillet cook meat and garlic until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained kidney beans, taco sauce and chili powder.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except roast.
Mix well. Add roast to mixture, turning to coat completely.
Cover and refrigerate for about 36 hours.
Turn meat twice daily.
Remove meat; strain, reserving marinade.
Pat dry meat.
In a Dutch oven, brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add marinade; cover and cook slowly 2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat.
For each cup of gravy desired, combine 3/4 cup meat juice and 1/4 cup water; add 1/3 cup broken gingersnaps and cook and stir until thick.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil.
Add the beef and cook, turning as needed, until browned, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a plate.
Spray the skillet with nonstick spray; heat.
Add the onion and garlic; cook, stirring, as needed until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until the flour is lightly browned, about 1 minute.

title: banbury tarts
directions: Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add other ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Chill dough.

title: mayonnaise from grandma's kitchen
directions: Place eggs in blender with salt, mustard and paprika.
Blend 30 seconds.
