Add vinegar and blend until smooth.
While blending, add 1 1/2 cups oil in slow steady stream.
When well blended, add 1/2 cup oil and lemon juice until completely mixed.
Lastly, add hot water, 2 drops at a time for smooth consistency.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef with next 8 ingredients.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meatballs. Drain.
Heat chili sauce and jelly together until all melted.
Add meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered.
Serve.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: coconut pecan fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease small cookie sheet.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 strips.
Pour milk into pie plate.
Mix coconut and pecans.
Dip bread strips into milk, then roll in coconut mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Makes 4 servings, about 285 calories.

title: lemon potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, slice potatoes lengthwise.
Place in baking dish with white facing up.
Mix lemon juice, water and olive oil.
Pour over potatoes, salt and pepper, then dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Good with Lemon Chicken.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Dice onion and green pepper; saute in small amount of oil.
Add vegeburger and brown slightly.
After browning, put in casserole dish and add can of soup.
Add a little water, approximately 1/4 cup or less, to make a little moist.
Top with crispy noodles. Cover and bake 1/2 hour or until hot.
Serve with frozen peas, rice and salad.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in the bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Sift the dry ingredients and mix into creamed mixture.
Pour into a loaf pan; bake 50 or 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Next, cool on rack.

title: mother's oat bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 muffins.
I find the pumpkin is best.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Combine Bisquick, Cheddar cheese, sausage and spices.
Knead in bowl to form a stiff dough.
Keeping peppers whole, stuff Monterey cheese into peppers. Take a small handful of dough and shape around each pepper to completely seal it inside.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put 3 tablespoons of the pineapple and all other ingredients into blender.
Blend 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Top with remaining pineapple and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve hot.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cornbread mix last.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: julie's brisket
directions: Saute diced garlic clove and remove from pot.
Put brisket; add carrots, celery and onions.
Spread with horseradish. Sprinkle with brown sugar; add 1 cup consomme and roast covered about 3 hours in 350° oven.
Spread with ketchup and brown sugar and brown at 450°.
Cool.
Skin fat, strain sauce or put through processor.
Can be frozen.
Defrost, slice and reheat.

title: chris's peanut butter squares
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar.
Spread in greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over top.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Tastes like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: A bit of brown sugar helps the taste.
Oregano adds a pleasant taste.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix salt, eggs and milk in a blender until frothy.
Very slowly add flour and mix until well blended.
Heat lard (or beef fat) in a 9-inch pie or cake pan until completely melted.
Pour batter into pan while it is very hot.
Cook for about 25 minutes or until golden brown and well risen on the sides.
Serve as an accompaniment to roast beef.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn, milk and oysters.
Gradually stir in egg and 1 cup of crumbs, onion and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Melt butter and mix with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave red sausage and rice
directions: Put all ingredients together into 2 quart glass bowl.
Cook on High 5-7 minutes or until boiling.
Put lid on and cook on power level 50 for 20 minutes.

title: cloud nine sponge cake
directions: Cake for strawberries.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until thick, about 3 minutes on high speed on mixer.
Gradually add sugar and beat on medium speed 3 to 5 minutes.
Fold dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Add butter to hot milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: braised lamb shanks
directions: Cut a vertical slit 1 1/2 inches deep in each shank; insert a clove of garlic.
Roll shank in mixture of 2 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Brown in fat; remove shanks.
Add 1/4 cup flour to fat and blend.
Stir in butter. Cook until thick, stirring.
Season with salt, pepper and Kitchen Bouquet.
Add shanks to gravy.
Cover; bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Raisin Rice.
Serves 4.

title: swiss cheese quickies
directions: Mix together and spread onto small rye bread slices.
Top with a slice of Swiss cheese and broil 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.

title: nut roll filling(povitica)
directions: Combine ingredients in a pan on low heat on stove.
Stir occasionally until fairly thick, about 25 or 30 minutes.
Take off burner.
Let cool.
Use any sweet dough.
Roll thin on floured tablecloth on table.
After rolled out, spread cinnamon and a little sugar all over dough.
Spread walnut filling all over to edges.
Take little dabs butter or oleo and throw here and there all over before you roll up.
Seal good on edges.
Place in a greased on pan or dish.
Let rise about an hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Place quartered pieces in a paper bag with cinnamon and sugar. Shake.
Put sugared pieces in ungreased Bundt pan.
Can add nuts to this as you go along.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat ingredients until stiff.
Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 more minutes or until set.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan or tube pan.
In large mixing bowl, mix by hand or with mixer first 4 ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Do not test doneness with toothpick.
It should spring back when touched lightly with fingertips.

title: lobster dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and mayo.
Gradually add liquid from lobster.
Mix until smooth. Add lobster and stir.

title: japanese raisin pie
directions: Mix together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Brown chops well on both sides in a frying pan.
Put chops in an ovenproof dish and place a big slice of unpared apple on each and on top of these, place orange slices, held together by a toothpick.
Add beef bouillon, cinnamon, cloves, brown sugar, cornstarch and orange juice.
Spread this on the meat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green pickled tomatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and hot peppers in large saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Add tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Continue to simmer while quickly packing one-half jar at a time.
Fill jar within 1/2-inch from top, making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Cap at once.
Process five minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: anise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 2 mounds, one on each baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until the mounds brown lightly and are fairly firm in the center.
Reverse the sheets on the oven racks after 15 minutes so that browning is even; remove.
Cut away edges to make mounds square.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Turn each strip on one cut side; bake for 10 minutes. Bake on other cut side for 10 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cut up bacon and brown; remove bacon and add diced onions and saute.
Drain butter beans and kidney beans; combine pork and beans.
Add ketchup, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dates and boiling water; set aside.
Mix the next 7 ingredients.
Add date mixture.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle over top before baking the chocolate chips, walnuts and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
These potatoes may be frozen or refrigerated before use.
Approximately 1 hour before baking, add a little milk to fluff and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: broiled stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat broiler.
Remove and chop the mushroom stems.
In a skillet, heat one tablespoon of the butter, add the onions and chopped mushroom stems and cook about two minutes.
Add the crumbs, the meat, shrimp or nuts, enough cream or sherry to moisten the mixture and the seasonings.
Place the mushroom caps on a baking sheet and brush with the remaining butter, melted.
Broil, cup side down, in a preheated broiler about two minutes.
Invert and fill with the stuffing.
Brush with melted butter and broil about three minutes longer.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender.
Drain and put in a buttered casserole.
Drain asparagus and place over vegetables. Add celery soup and spread over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Place all the ingredients in a plastic food storage bag. Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking pan; discard bag.
Bake at 400°, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley. Makes about 8 servings.

title: potato chip butter cookies
directions: Soften	butter;
mix
with
sugar and vanilla, then add chips and flour.	Drop
by
teaspoonfuls	on
ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.	Dust with powdered sugar.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all of the above together.
Refrigerate.
Good to use with fresh vegetables.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: About 4 hours before, in an 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef in salad oil until browned on both sides.
Remove meat.
Add to drippings in pan, onions and garlic; cook until lightly brown, about 5 minutes.
Spoon off drippings.
Stir in tomato sauce and remaining ingredients to the onion and garlic mixture in pan.
Put meat back in Dutch oven.
Heat on high to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 3 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Turn meat once during this time.
To serve, remove meat to deep platter, skim off fat from liquid in Dutch oven and discard bay leaves.
Spoon remaining liquid over meat.

title: nutty baked apple
directions: Add enough water to a 9 x 5-inch microwave-safe loaf pan to fill about 1/4-inch.
Core apples.
Peel a 1-inch strip of skin off top of apples.
Arrange apples in pan, evenly spaced.
Place 1 teaspoon of the butter and 1/2 teaspoon of the brown sugar into each apple.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, rotating dish once, until apples are tender.
Remove from oven and let stand, covered, 2 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Add water to raisins and cook until 1 cup of water is left. Cool.

title: cool shrimp pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on bottom of 12 inch greased pizza pan. Bake at 375° for 11-13 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and dill weed.
Spread over crust.
Top with cocktail sauce, then shrimp, and end with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and chill for 2-24 hours before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
This is good with fresh vegetables.

title: heath bars
directions: Fishing trips to old Kernville.
We took our food and bought root beer at the old Brown Store.
It was surrounded by trees and was always very cool, so we could eat our lunch there under the trees.
We fished in the Kern River close by.
The fish was sure better than the fish you can catch today out of the lake!!!

title: mom's sugar cookies(tea cakes)
directions: Cream lard, sugar and eggs.
Sift 2 cups flour with soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milks.
Add enough more flour to make a dough as soft as can be handled.
Roll out rather thin.
Cut with a large cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° until just firm to touch.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until center is done.

title: black beans
directions: Cook the soaked beans in water for an hour or until tender. Saute the onion, garlic, pepper and tomato in oil for about 3 minutes.
Add the sauteed mixture and cumin to the beans; cover and cook on low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add the lemon juice just before serving over rice.

title: gourmet hominy bake
directions: Drain and rinse hominy.
Generously grease with butter, a 3-quart casserole.
Layer following ingredients in order: hominy (use 1/2), 1/2 green chilies, minced; season with salt and pepper. Dot generously with sour cream and butter.
Repeat layers; dot with sour cream and butter.
Pour cream over all.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve piping hot.
Good with steak instead of baked potatoes.

title: potato salad german style
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry crisp.
Pour off all fat, except 2 tablespoons.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring constantly.
Add hot water, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over potatoes and toss gently.
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: no bake oatmeal chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and butter on stove at hard boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Let sit until hard.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa and boil in saucepan for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oats.
Mix and drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: prune sunburst
directions: Whip whipping cream, gradually adding sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold
in	prunes,
pineapple,
coconut and nuts. Chill several hours before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: tomatoes and eggplant
directions: Cut 1 large eggplant in cubes after peeling.
Cover with salt water and let boil until soft, doesn't take long.
Pour all water off; mix with stewed tomatoes.
Cube about 1/4 pound sharp cheese and stir mixture.
Put in casserole; put bread cubes, grated sharp cheese and a little butter on top.
Brown in broiler.
Add a little oregano and sweet basil on top.
Delicious!

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in slow cooker.
Stir well to coat steak.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook on high 1 hour, then turn to low and cook 8 hours.

title: zucchini soup(sopa de calabaza)
directions: Boil cut zucchini in water with cilantro just until soft. Drain.
In a soup pot, heat butter and saute blanched zucchini. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken stock and milk. Cook until zucchini is very soft, about 15 minutes.
Puree. Before serving, add corn and poblano chile to taste.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Take sausage from casing and brown.
Bring water to boil and add sliced zucchini.
Parboil for a few minutes.
Chop and saute green pepper.
Slice zucchini, some of the spices, onion, pepper, 2 cheeses and sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, covered.

title: pine nut crusted chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, pine nuts and parsley in a mixing bowl. Lightly flour chicken breasts.
Dip them into the egg whites and then into the bread crumb mixture.
Heat olive oil in skillet and saute breaded chicken until cooked through (about 5 to 8 minutes on each side).

title: cherry chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars thoroughly; add egg and vanilla, beating well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts, then cherries and chocolate chips; stir to blend well.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with half a cherry, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: In saucepan, mix the brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard, salt and
coffee.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In a 12-inch casserole, layer the beans, sliced onion and half of the sauce.
Repeat. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Beans will keep moist and warm for several hours if covered with foil and left in a 200° oven.

title: calcium kick shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
(602 mg calcium, 1 g fat)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust. Bake at 450° for 6-8 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 50-60 minutes longer.

title: louise mark's cranberry marble salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Stir in cranberry sauce.

title: reuben mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems.
Arrange half the mushrooms, stem
side up, on a 10 or 12-inch round microwave-safe plate. Cover with plastic.
Cook on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until almost tender.
Invert caps on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining caps.

title: no-bake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler on low heat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill 8 hours.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Place apples and onions around the chops.
Mix water, catsup and brown sugar. Mix this and pour over the apples, onions and chops.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
You may have to add a little more sauce if it dries out too much.

title: orange candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain, cool, peel and cut lengthwise.
Set aside.
Melt butter in skillet; stir in marmalade, orange juice, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes.
Cook uncovered for 15 minutes, turning occasionally. Put in serving bowl.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: gram's mustard dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve as dip with crisp vegetables or strips of cooked meat.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: jubilee cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except Brazil nuts and chocolate pieces.
Blend well at low speed.
Stir in 1/2 cup Brazil nuts; mix thoroughly.
Chill dough for easier handling.
Shape into balls, using rounded teaspoonful for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press candy kiss or 5 chocolate chips into center of hot cookie.
When chocolate has softened, spread to frost.
Sprinkle with remaining chopped nuts. Makes about 36 cookies.

title: french fry batter
directions: Combine dry ingredients together.
Add milk and egg and beat until smooth.
This batter may be used for onion rings, fish, chicken, green beans, okra, carrots and mushrooms.
Best if you fry in deep fat such as a Fry Daddy.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour half of batter in 9-inch pan.
Seed jalapeno peppers and cut open one side.
Lay flat on top of batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Top with remaining batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: donna and karen's sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Form 36 balls.
Bake in a 9-inch square glass dish for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Use a microwavable bowl.
Mix cocoa and sugar.
Lay the butter on top of mixture.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out and add pecans.
Add milk if needed- pour out onto buttered plater. Refrigerate until hard.
Cut into squares.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell 400 for 7 minutes.
Put basil on bottom of pie shell, peel tomatoes and cut up.
Add rest of ingredients to tomatoes and fold together.

title: angel food fluff
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time to butter and sugar, then add the juice of the lemon and grated lemon rind.
Beat the egg whites and fold into mixture. Whip the whipping cream and fold in last.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cake dish with sliced cake.
Spread half of the filling over cake layer. Place another layer of cake over filling, then rest of filling over cake, then top filling with another layer of cake.
With another 1/2 pint of whipping cream and then spread over last layer of cake. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate.
Cut into pieces to serve. May place maraschino cherry on top of each piece.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk in a baking dish; add butter.
In a saucepan, bring peaches to a hard boil.
Pour over mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: baked pretzels
directions: Bake at 250° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: pearl's main dish noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Meanwhile, beat together the butter and cream cheese until blended.
Add egg yolks and sour cream and beat, scraping bowl and beaters several times until smooth.
Fold in the cooked, drained noodles.
With a clean beater, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in.

title: john's hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Saute onions until tender.
Mix onions, ketchup, sugar, mustard, tomatoes and soup.
Add the following ingredients to taste:
salt, celery salt, garlic powder, pepper and parsley flakes.
May also add barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce or steak sauce for more flavor.
Dash of this and that. Cook in heavy pan until desired consistency.

title: broccoli surprise
directions: Place the
broccoli in baking dish.
Mix the rest of the ingredients over low heat until blended.
Pour over the broccoli and bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: mexican delight
directions: Cook the ingredients 30 minutes after the rice is added.
Cook slowly and stir often.
Serve over Fritos.
Garnish with grated cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce, chopped green olives, chopped onions and a hot sauce made with catsup, Tabasco, cocktail sauce, Worcestershire, etc.
Use as much or as little of any or all of the garnishes as you like.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add Ro-Tel (use half the juice if you want it less spicy).
Add soups and cheese and cook until blended. Spray 13 x 9-inch dish with Pam.
Layer 1/2 Doritos, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 sauce and repeat.
Bake at 400° until cheese bubbles and slightly browned.

title: broccoli and cauliflower chowder
directions: Heat butter and oil in soup pot over medium low heat.
Add leeks.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until very soft.
Add garlic and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add diced pepper, broccoli, cauliflower, potato, chicken broth and all seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
(Mixture will be thick.) Turn heat down to simmer and cook, covered, 35 minutes or until veggies are very tender.
Add evaporated skim milk and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage dressing
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; add to salad oil.

title: barbie's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a baking dish (oblong casserole dish, etc.) and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly hot (usually 20 to 30 minutes).

title: diabetic walnut brownies
directions: Spray 8-inch square cake pan with nonstick spray.
Combine cake mix, egg yolk, water and vanilla in a small bowl.
Stir to completely blend.
Transfer mixture to pan and sprinkle lightly with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
After baking, cut and remove from pan to cooling rack.

title: peppermint stick bars
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in chocolate pieces.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan. Beat egg white until frothy.
Brush over bars. Sprinkle crushed candy over bars.
Bake until golden brown in a 350° oven, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars. Makes about 40 bars.

title: savory scramblers
directions: Spray a skillet (preferably nonstick) with the nonstick spray.

Mix the 3 medium eggs with the egg substitute. Combine that mixture with the Parmesan cheese, garlic, dill, chives, parsley and tomatoes. Place the prepared skillet over medium heat and carefully pour in the egg mixture. Turn the egg mixture gently with a spatula as it cooks. As the eggs begin to set, stir them a few times until they are firm. (Because of safety concerns, it is not a good idea to serve runny eggs.) Divide the eggs into four attractive serving dishes. Place a lettuce leaf under each serving, if you wish.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Mix next 4 ingredients. Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Pour into a fondue pot and keep warm.
Serve with fresh strawberries.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7 to 8-inch spring-form pan.
Crumbs stick when a little Pam is sprayed. Using knife blade in food processor bowl, combine cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, processing until smooth.
Add egg and process just until blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients; line loaf pan with wax paper.
With hands, mold ingredients into pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Base:
Combine gelatin, boiling water, 7-Up, drained pineapple and sliced bananas.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan.
Melt brown sugar and margarine. Pour over biscuits.
May add chopped walnuts or pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread thick coating of peanut butter over cake. Refrigerate until peanut butter hardens.
Melt chocolate bar and spread over cake with spatula.

title: wild sex on the beach
directions: Mix and serve over ice.
This is good.

title: whole grain pancakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg whites, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: oil roasted summer vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and dry vegetables, leaving stems intact and arrange them in a shallow baking dish just large enough to hold them in a single layer.
Drizzle with the olive oil, then sprinkle coarse salt over all.
(While it is possible to oversalt the dish, it can stand more salt than you think.)
Bake until brown and slightly shriveled.
Vegetables will not all cook at the same rate.
Zucchini and eggplant will be done in 30 minutes or so, potatoes an hour.

title: red beans and rice with smoked sausage
directions: Place all ingredients, except sausage and rice, in 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer. Cover and cook for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add sausage to red bean mixture the last 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: peaches 'n cream dessert
directions: Make crust of butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Put in a 9 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Put scant 1/2 cup of sugar in peaches; set aside.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, salt, cornstarch and water; cook until clear and thick.
Add gelatin and dissolve.
Allow to cool, then add peaches.
Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually add milk; continue to beat.
Fold in topping.
Put 1/2 cream cheese mixture over crust.
Add peaches.
Top with remaining cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.

title: chow down
directions: Melt the butter, peanut butter and chocolate morsels in the microwave for 2 minutes or until melted.
Pour the cereal into a large bowl.
Pour the chocolate mixture over the cereal.
Put the chocolate covered cereal in a large paper bag and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Close the paper bag and shake until contents are covered with the sugar.
Enjoy!

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Put the ribs in a large saucepan with enough water to cover ribs. Cover saucepan and simmer 1 hour.

title: blueberry tea loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, sour cream, lemon peel, vanilla, and nutmeg, beating until smooth. Gradually beat in dry ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Using spatula, gently spread the batter into the pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
(If top is getting too brown, cover with foil.)
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Beat eggs, add to creamed mixture. Stir in flour and sour milk.
Mix in hot water and cocoa to form a smooth paste.
Pour this into batter and pour all into a 2-layer cake pan or an angel food cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued pork chinese style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove fat from meat.
Combine soy sauce, wine, sugar, honey, food coloring, cinnamon, garlic and onion.
In large bowl, add pork, turning to coat completely. Cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour or refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain pork; reserve marinade. Place pork on wire rack over baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven until done, about 45 minutes.
Turn and baste frequently during baking.
To serve, cut into diagonal slices (like London broil).

title: mexican caldo
directions: Place all ingredients into pot, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until all ingredients are tender.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix hash browns, chopped onions and sour cream together. Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 1 stick of oleo, soup and shredded cheese.
Spread on top of potato mixture. Mix together corn flakes and 1 stick of oleo.
Sprinkle on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover 20 minutes.
Mix margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar/oats mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Can sprinkle with powdered sugar when done or frost.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Combine boiled potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and onion powder.
Whip or mash until fluffy.
Add small amount of milk, if necessary.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole and refrigerate or freeze until needed.

title: chocolate candies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Let cool about 5 minutes. When cool, stir in mini marshmallows and finely chopped nuts.
Do not melt marshmallows.
Makes 2 loaves approximately 2 inches in diameter.
Chill about 15 minutes.
Roll in additional chopped nuts.
Chill overnight, cut as desired.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook chicken, saving broth.
Fry sausage (15 minutes).
Add onions, peppers and celery to chicken broth and tomato juice. Bring to a boil.
Add parsley flakes, green onions, chicken and sausage and bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Add water if too dry. Cover pot and cook on low heat for approximately 40 to 50 minutes. (Every 20 or 25 minutes, stir twice, turning rice from bottom of pot.)
Additional water may be needed throughout cooking time. Will serve at least 15 people.
Delicious!

title: strudel
directions: Beat eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients.
Let stand 30 minutes. Place dough on board floured with cake meal.
Put more cake meal on dough.
Pat thin.
Spread with jelly and nuts.
Bake on oil greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked penne rigati
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Prepare penne rigati as package directions.
In large bowl, combine penne rigati, sausage, pasta sauce and 2 cups cheese, mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish; cover.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly; uncover, top with remaining 2 c. cheese and parsley; refrigerate left over.

title: chocolate-peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil and cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Gradually add oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto aluminum foil; allow to cool.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk and salt.
Add the cubed bread, cooked sausage and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover; set in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaetzle(a perfect accompaniment to bavarian casserole recipe)
directions: Beat eggs and add to mixed dry ingredients.
Add water.
Drop mixture into boiling water to cook.
To make spaetzle, I use an old metal pie pan that has 3/8 inch holes drilled into the bottom.
I spray it with Pam and place it over the saucepan of boiling water and use a flat spatula to force the dough through the holes.
This makes nice round little spaetzle.
Remove to cold water to stop the cooking process until you are ready to serve.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Trim fat from the chops and heat the fat in a skillet.
When you have about 2 tablespoons of fat, remove the trimmings.
Brown chops in fat and season with salt and pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 60 minutes or until the chops are done.

title: bran muffins
directions: This makes 6 dozen and can be stored in Tupperware container in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Just use what you need and refrigerate the rest.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add margarine.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.
Divide into two parts. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with small cookie cutter. Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: skillet green beans
directions: Put oil in skillet & heat add green beans and seasoning. Saute on med./high heat for 5-10 minutes, stir.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Before you start your cake, put the angel food pan into the oven which should be set at 400°.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until stiff.
Fold in granulated sugar and vanilla.
Sift together, the flour and powdered sugar.
Fold into the mixture.
Pour into hot pan.
Bake at 425° for 23 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat lemon jello, eggs, water and lemon juice for 2 minutes. Add cake mix and salad oil.
Beat until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in angel food or oblong pan.

title: rock candy
directions: Cook until when tested is at hard ball stage, then pour in greased unlined cupcake pans.
